Our vision is to become the next AirBnB of the food industry!

Aquestia provides products and software solutions for surge protection, water loss reduction, and pressure management.
Aquestia operates in a large number of segments, including waterworks distribution systems; agriculture, gardening, and landscape; wastewater transmission systems; industrial applications in mining, ballast water, and desalination; fire protection; aviation fueling; commercial plumbing; water treatment and filtration; and water metering.

NanoAF develops biocompatible and environmentally friendly materials that resist biofouling. The materials are based on short peptides that can self-assemble into a film for coating surfaces. Using peptides for this purpose is advantageous due to the peptides’ biocompatibility, chemical diversity, and ability to be easily synthesized on a large scale.
NanoAF’s solution is biofriendly, nontoxic, and non-biocidal. It can be used in numerous applications, including mold prevention, air-quality control, marine antifouling, food packaging, medical-device protection, and water treatment.

The systems are designed to meet a variety of security needs by emphasizing interoperability, survivability, and ease of use. The company's drones provide full intelligence, surveillance, target acquisition, and reconnaissance services.
Aero Sentinel's systems detect and assess threats, manage information, and support first responders while also simplifying the coordination of deployed assets and contributing information to situation reports and decision-making processes at all leadership levels.

OriginGPS develops, manufactures, and supplies some of the world’s smallest GNSS and cellular IoT solutions. Its high-performance miniature GNSS products provide multiple constellation support to help users track everything valuable to their businesses.
The company’s OriginIoT is designed to make IoT-enabling devices affordable and accessible by eliminating the need for additional embedded software and RF engineering know-how. The low-power cellular IoT system reduces project costs and dramatically shortens time to market in the development of cellular IoT devices.

Ooval Valves develops, manufactures, and markets self-actuating hydraulic control valves for water-based and foam-based systems used in waterworks, fire protection, oil and gas, petrochemical, power plant, and mining applications.
The company has over three decades of professional expertise in management, development, marketing, and technical support for hydraulic control valves.

SemiConductor Devices (SCD) is a supplier of high-end infrared detectors and laser diodes. Backed by more than 30 years of accumulated experience, SCD’s products have been chosen by companies worldwide for use in their high-end electro-optical systems.
SCD has a vertically integrated production structure that allows strict quality control throughout the various processes, from crystal growth to device packaging and testing. Its in-house capabilities include semiconductor processing, LPE and MBE growth, VLSI design, Dewar and vacuum technology, assembly and radiometric modeling, and testing.

Solid Applied Technologies Ltd (SolidAT) produces sensors and remote monitoring solutions for managing flow, pressure, level, and volume in industrial plants and waterways. SolidAT's sensors are non-contact and utilize ultrasonic technology.
The company's remote monitoring systems are based on GPRS cellular communications and a web-based monitoring application. Ultrasonic sensor technology is well suited for challenging applications such as sewage, corrosive chemicals, and rivers.

Ayecka Communication Systems provides cost-effective solutions for the delivery of IP and video over satellite links. The company has developed new technologies to boost performance, including its RFModem and the HW Accelerator.
Ayecka currently focuses on two markets: the professional market for its SCPC products and the consumer market for its smartLNB and RFModem, which delivers the company's technology for interactive TV, smart LNB, smart grid, smart home, and the Internet of Things.

ScoutCam is the developer of a visualization and AI platform for predictive maintenance and condition-based monitoring, providing maintenance and operations teams visibility into areas inaccessible under normal operations or environmentally unsuitable for continuous real-time monitoring.
ScoutCam’s camera-as-a-sensor technology, in conjunction with specialized AI models, is currently deployed in hard-to-reach locations and harsh environments across a variety of predictive maintenance and condition-based monitoring use cases in markets including aviation, energy, mobility, and transportation.

RADWIN is a global provider of wireless solutions that aim to deliver fast broadband with exceptional reliability. RADWIN's solutions are equipped with powerful operational support tools that support all operational aspects of the network lifecycle and enable operation in the toughest conditions, including interference and non-line-of-sight.
Deployed in over 170 countries, the company's solutions power applications including backhaul, broadband access, private network connectivity, and video surveillance transmission, and deliver mobile broadband for trains, vehicles, and marine vessels.

column3:
Ramim Environmental Resources develops a closed, automated, in situ composting process that turns sludge into class-A compost in three to five days.
Ramim’s process is based on a modification of the rotating drum technique. The company arranges a processing line that combines dehydrated industrial sludge with a bulking agent. The combined materials are then rotated in a drum at controlled temperatures for up to five days, creating high-quality compost suitable for agriculture.

WATA Solution seeks to help households in developing countries monitor their water quantity and quality. Using low-cost sensors, WATA Solution provides consumers, water companies, and municipalities with instant access to data on water purity, supply remaining, and other information essential to daily living.

CleaRivers offers complex microbial solutions and systems designed to absorb, metabolize, and convert many organic and inorganic pollutants in order to purify water. Its technologies consume no external energy and offer low construction, maintenance, and operational costs.
CleaRivers’ flagship product is MicrobiaMix, a system designed to purify and clean polluted rivers, take wastewater to the tertiary level, and make the water available for agricultural uses.

Resorcix specializes in providing solutions and product development to address bacteria in the food and beverage industry. Its antimicrobial approach is designed to allow products to reach a longer shelf life with no spoilage.
The company's technology is environmentally friendly and based on the medicinal chemistry of natural products. The Resorcix research project explores a natural anti-spore-forming bacteria agent for use in the natural beverage industry to expand the potential shelf life to that of other food industry products, such as chocolate and meat.

Drone Master is software designed for professional, high-end drone and unmanned aerial vehicle users. Drone Master offers fleet management solutions for medium and large organizations that run complex drone operations, including flight operations, technical maintenance activities, and client and project management.
Drone Master gives businesses smart tools to run their operation and track maintenance activities effectively and safely, in compliance with civil aviation authorities' requirements.

Amraz specializes in producing plastic packaging and finished products from a wide range of thermoplastic raw materials.
The company offers an extensive array of advanced production methods, such as thin film injection molding, technical injection molding, co-extrusion, extrusion of multilayer foils and multicolor striped foils, hot fill, and in-mold labeling (IML).

Intelescope Solutions is a forest-analytics company that uses drone and satellite imagery, software, and expert analysis to evaluate timber resources for clients such as forestry land owners, managers and consultants, timber REITs, TIMOs, and pension and hedge funds, 
The company uses patented algorithms that fuse precise positioning information with pan- and multi-spectral imaging to provide clients with automated services at speeds that are 50-100x faster than current processing techniques, enabling more efficient management and a richer knowledge of timber assets.

column3: Greeneng Solutions offers ozone-based solutions to reduce the use of chemicals for disinfection in the food industry, agriculture, water treatment, industrial processes, wastewater treatment, treatment and recycling of greywater, disinfection of pools and reservoirs, biofilm and algae control, and sterilization of medical and laboratory equipment.

meshek{76}; is engaged in the exploration, development, and optimization of autonomous and sustainable agriculture. Using artificial-intelligence technologies that can make decisions independently, meshek{76}; seeks to transfer food production management and handling from people to coordinated and accurate autonomous systems.
The company's core technology stems from the ideological principles of open-source and collaborative development, through which it develops and implements a wide range of comprehensive solutions for the automation of production processes in greenhouse farming.
column11: americas, north america, central america, europe, asia

column3:
PMK developed an environmentally friendly process to convert municipal sludge into class-A compost within a few hours at a low cost, with virtually no investment in CAPEX or energy consumption.
A small scale pilot in WWTP Jerusalem was successfully conducted in accordance with Israel Ministry of Environmental Protection guidelines.

Nutrilees is working to create an affordable and sustainable food source that contains proteins, dietary fibers, and minerals out of industrial wine residue. This upcycled byproduct can be incorporated in a large variety of food applications; offers a neutral taste; and is non-allergenic, gluten free, and vegan.

Rootility develops and implements root-focused plant-breeding methods designed to increase crop yields and overall agronomic performance while preserving crop quality. Rootility's selection system improves plants' root traits, improving their access to water and nutrients and resulting in crop tolerance to abiotic stresses such as cold, heat, drought, and soil salinity.
The system functions without genetic modification and is applicable to a broad range of crops including tomatoes, sunflowers, peppers, melons, and corn.

Ovo Technology is the developer of a sex-reversal technology for the broiler industry, where males are considered more profitable and economically efficient than females. The company’s solution is a natural material composition that is injected directly into chicken embryos to promote the development of female broilers that function like males in terms of weight gain and feed conversion ratio. The materials used are safe for human consumption in large doses.

AquaPure uses proprietary non-thermal plasma technology to remove micropollutants from contaminated groundwater for the municipal and groundwater treatment markets.
The company offers an ozone (hydroxyl radicals) UV advanced oxidation process water treatment solution, allowing for effective purification of water contaminants such as volatile organic compounds. The chemical-free technology is safe for users and the environment.

Cannpany is using patented technology to develop the Cannpany Cultivation Center for cannabis cultivation. The company’s platform is designed to increase profits and yields at a lower operating cost than other cultivation centers.
The company’s technology enables the operation of a field of dual-sided panels mounted on solar trackers. One side is a mirror (heliostat) that guides natural light through the solar reflecting tower to the plants; the second side is a photovoltaic (PV) panel producing clean power. As solar radiation changes seasonally and hourly, the dual-sided tracker solution allows the company’s software, based on a heliostat/PV ratio algorithm, to optimize the growth potential of the plant while using any surplus solar radiation to produce clean power.

eggXYt is developing a CRISPR-based proprietary technology that detects the sex of chick embryos immediately after the eggs are laid and before they enter the 21-day incubation period.
The sex-identification process prevents chicks from hatching unnecessarily; keeps the eggs within the food industry; and addresses the common ethical, environmental, and economic problems of egg and poultry production. eggXYt saves many chicks a year by preventing their unnecessary incubation, which typically requires employees at the end of the hatchery line to identify and kill male chicks.

Otaiot specializes in developing and manufacturing drone technology for autonomous air missions. The company’s autonomous drone platform includes a drone and base station unit, an autonomous flight controller, and a central arial system for airborne drone management.

Poiike Foodtec is developing a step-by-step digital cooking guide. Proprietary algorithms and artificial intelligence power the platform, orchestrating the creation of a whole meal. This guide helps users find recipes, make shopping lists, organize the kitchen work, keep track of cooking times, and more.
Kinoko-Tech develops fermentation products based on fungal mycelium that grows on legumes and grains, offering a solution for the rise in market demand for alternative proteins.

Soos Technology is a biotechnology company focused on reducing male layer extermination and improving the production capacity in commercial hatcheries. Soos Technology’s solution affects the genetic expression of the reproductive system in genetic male layer embryos and can turn male layers into functional female layers capable of laying eggs.
The company’s AI-guided incubation system uses a patented combination of temperature, humidity, CO2, and sonic vibrations to control the sex development process in poultry embryos. The solution does not use GMOs, gene editing, or any hormonal interventions. As in other species in nature, the solution mirrors a completely natural process of sexual differentiation driven by changes in environmental conditions.

UniVerve is developing a flexible and scalable micro-algae biomass production technology that enables the use of micro-algae biomass as feedstock for the food, feed, and bio-based industries.
The company's technology is designed to cover the entire production process. Its projects are based on the micro-algae genus Nannochloropsis and include micro-algae oil high in omega-3 fatty acids (EPA), protein-rich biomass, and extracts beneficial for health and cosmetic purposes.
column12: havp™ cultivation system (hanging adjustable v-shaped pond)

column3:
WaterSheer provides water purification and distribution systems and solutions, mainly for water-challenged regions and crisis situations. WaterSheer's purification systems treat organic, biologic, and chemical water contaminators.
The emergency product line provides comprehensive solutions for situations such as natural disasters, temporary lack of drinking water, difficulties in distributing water, supplying water to moving forces, and humanitarian aid efforts.

NanoPure Plasma is developing a UV disinfection and oxidation system utilizing a hydrodynamic structure and photo-catalytic coating, enabling a reduction in the cost to treat and the ability to operate in environmental conditions that did not previously allow the use of UV technology.
NanoPure Plasma's technology can be used in a broad range of applications in the fields of food and beverage manufacturing, wastewater third-level treatment, oil drilling, water recycling, etc.

Genaphora has developed real-time, quantitative PCR (qPCR) and end-point PCR diagnostic kits. The company has developed its own computational biology platform employing thermodynamics calculations and modifications of linguistic complexity. Genaphora’s approach ensures the best fit primers and probes out of a whole genome sequence of any given organism, resulting in greater sensitivity and specificity.

Blue I Water Technologies develops, designs, manufactures, and markets online and smart water-quality analysis and control systems. The company’s patented technologies include water quality analyzers and controllers for industrial and municipal applications and swimming pools.
Blue I’s products offer complete analysis, dosing, and control while ensuring low maintenance and costs. Its analyzers are based on electro-optical IP technology and control algorithms designed to ensure high-precision chemical monitoring and control.

column3:
Biomonitech provides early-warning systems for water supply contamination using a network of luminescent biosensors. The company utilizes nonpathogenic, luminous marine bacteria as highly responsive sensors that can rapidly indicate changes in water quality.
Biomonitech's technology offers bioassays that enable long-term storage, are highly sensitive to low concentrations of a range of contaminants, and provide reliable and consistent results within minutes.

Verstill develops production equipment capable of producing spirits quickly and cost-effectively. The company has two technologies: the Versatile still, which can control product flavor by modifying the internal reacting array in the still, and a hyperaging technology that accelerates the naturally occurring reactions in order to create spirits in a matter of weeks.

Rilbite technology mixes and binds clean and fresh plant ingredients into dishes of different shapes, textures, and tastes, creating plant-based meat analogs for meat, egg, ice cream, chicken, or fish.
The company's fully developed product, Minced Plants, is a blend of five fresh ingredients equivalent to minced meat based on Rilbite's platform and powered by the company's culinary technology. The company already has a full-scale manufacturing automatic production line for this product.

FiltoFlex has developed a filtration system based on flexible filtration media that can change its shape under controlled pressure, enabling control of the filtration grade to achieve efficient backwash and reduce the total filtration cost. FiltoFlex filters can be implemented in applications such as drinking water filtration, desalination pretreatment, and secondary wastewater filtration.

AquaSpark provides comprehensive, cost-efficient wastewater treatment solutions for industrial, agricultural, and municipal applications. AquaSpark's solutions combine its Boiling Layer Treatment Technology (BLTT) for treatment of wastewater with high contents of organic contaminants. AquaSpark's BLTT applies electric power in a specific regime, causing several phenomena to occur locally within the treated wastewater. Local micro-sparks lead to discharge of ozone, UV radiation, and micro-impulses of pressure. Consequently the organic content of wastewater decomposes into gases and a small amount of cinder.

Bayit Legan has developed the Macrophytic Artificial Mini-wetland (MAM) system, in which household greywater is purified by macrophytic means.
With the MAM system, greywater is discharged after use from kitchen and bathroom sinks, showers, baths, dishwashers, and washing machines, and then flows from the home to an artificially created mini-wetland, passing through various layers of aggregates (e.g. sand, pebbles, etc.) along the way.

WTR Tec operates in the field of wastewater purification for domestic, industrial, and agricultural applications. Its technology is based on separating contaminants from water, rather than water from contaminants, using physical, electrochemical, and hydrodynamic methods.
WTR Tec implements methodologies that optimize the working point of the electrocoagulation and electrofloatation multivariable processes, resulting in a process that is energetically and operationally effective.

TreeTube develops and supplies products and solutions for urban greenery tree development. TreeTube enables conditions for planting trees under pavement in a low-cost, integrated system that includes soil, aeration, and irrigation systems.
TreeTube products provide the underground roots with direction and adequate balanced conditions, allowing trees to grow to their full potential without damaging adjacent city infrastructure. These solutions can change the way designers and urban planners use trees as an integral component of the city's infrastructure.

C-Valves develops robust control valves and pressure management systems designed to improve water stability and provide fewer bursts, reduce water loss, and lower maintenance and energy costs. The company offers solutions for waterworks and water treatment plants, desalination plants, irrigation systems, water-intensive industrial projects, and mining operations.
C-Valves is a subsidiary of Saisanket Ltd, an Indian water solutions company.

Treatec21 Industries engages in municipal, industrial, and agricultural water and wastewater treatment, designing and building new plants and upgrading existing ones. The company also offers water reusage solutions for urban development, residential landscaping, and public parks.
In 2010, Treatec21 merged with Yaad Industries.

column3: Nirosoft specializes in the design, manufacture, installation, operation, and maintenance of water and wastewater solutions. The company develops tailor-made systems that deliver water to densely populated areas, remote communities, and complex industrial sites. It can deploy emergency mobile water treatment units to disaster areas, treat and reuse wastewater, use desalination to supply potable water, and produce demineralized water for industry.

Whitewater Technologies develops technologies for the smart water network management software market, helping utilities better utilize data to gain operational efficiency, sustainability, and increased levels of customer service. 
Smart water network solutions improve the efficiency, longevity, and reliability of the underlying physical water network by better measuring, collecting, analyzing, and acting upon a wide range of network events. This can take shape in different phases of the utility process, such as real-time monitoring and automation, operational readiness, or network planning.

Together Pharma is setting up an agricultural cultivation system that will allow the control and supervision of cannabis plants using the latest technologies. The company's system is designed to develop quality plants suitable for supervised medical use according to the strict IMC-GAP standards of Israel's Ministry of Health.
Together Pharma has set up a skincare subsidiary in partnership with Israeli cosmetics and skincare company Premier Dead Sea Cosmetics Laboratories. The company has also signed long-term contract agreements to export cannabis to Germany and Canada.

column3: Hava helps create a direct connection between farmers and consumers. For farmers, Hava offers an increased marginal profit. Consumers can order fruits and vegetables through an app and have their order delivered directly to them.

Aleinu develops aeroponic farm facilities and systems. Its proprietary technologies are intended to increase the level of automation and efficiency in the farming process while eliminating many of the common problems of conventional farming, such as unpredictable weather, high land costs, and the need for long hours of outdoor labor by many workers.
Aleinu’s aeroponic systems and environmentally friendly greenhouses are designed to yield more produce and consume less water than traditional farms.

Cannatrix has developed a cloud-based system that helps cannabis growers better understand their crops by troubleshooting problems, enabling plants to reach their full potential.
The Cannatrix system collects data manually or by integrating with third-party APIs. It then analyzes the data and categorizes it according to classifications such as viruses, diseases, and crop maturity, and advises growers on how best to improve the growth process.
column11: south america, australia, canada, united states

column3:
GRiN Systems offers a smart eco-control system that aims to improve the yield and quality of homegrown cannabis through the use of a wide range of agricultural sensors and analytic tools. GRiN is suitable for a variety of soil-based indoor and outdoor growing techniques specifically aimed at small to medium-scale cannabis producers growing up to 10 plants.
The GRiN system helps create an optimal environment for the plants, ensuring a shorter lifecycle and quicker harvest. The system also monitors the precise amount of water and nutrients the plants require at each stage of the growth cycle.

Snacktive develops functional foods designed to aid digestion through the use of enzymatic and encapsulation technologies. Based on biochemical activity, Snacktive products can mitigate many commonly experienced problems with the digestive system, including irritable bowel syndrome and lack of satiety.
Snacktive belongs to the Profile Group of Companies.
foodYo connects food providers with private consumers and nonprofit organizations in order to eliminate the excess food market by aggregating and brokering excess food orders and deliveries.

Agrowatcher uses computer-vision technology and multispectral imaging to discern differences in crops in order to detect water stress, pests, infestation, and diseases.
The 24/7 system uses a digital camera that records reflected light energy imagery in multiple bands across the visible and near-infrared spectrum with significant resolution. Using bespoke computer vision algorithms and machine learning, the images are analyzed and a specific treatment (watering, pesticide/herbicide application, etc.) is administered immediately with plant-by-plant precision.

Mera Hawk provides cloud-based remote fertigation systems and quality hardware for continuous data gathering from anywhere, regardless of climate conditions or terrain.
Mera Hawk is a collaboration of agronomists, engineers, and IoT personnel aiming to remotely monitor all phases of commercial plant growth.

Agri-TAR designs, develops, and manufactures infrastructure and supporting appliances for agriculture, including solutions for irrigation, greenhouses, aquaculture, poultry farming, and dairy farming. The company also manufactures a line of LED grow lights.
Agri-TAR implements turnkey projects with feasibility studies and supervision, training and ongoing management, growing materials, construction, and support projects.

Nature Beta Technologies (NBT) cultivates Dunaliella bardawil microalgae, a source of beta carotene that contains 50% of the 9-cis isomer which occurs only in natural form. The microalgae is also rich in other carotenoids, such as phytoene, lutein, and lycopene, as well as other phytochemicals and micronutrients.
NBT is a subsidiary of the Nikken Sohonsha Corporation in Japan and the partner of D-factory, a consortium funded by the European Commission with the goal of setting a world benchmark for a sustainable CO2 algae biorefinery based on Dunaliella biomass.

Aromor Flavors & Fragrances develops, produces, and markets natural, natural-identical, and synthetic high-added-value aroma and flavor ingredients for the perfume, cosmetics, and food industries. The company specializes in the development of captives and sophisticated molecules.
Aromor has operated as a subsidiary of International Flavors & Fragrances Inc since 2014.

Horse Mate is a smart social engagement platform designed to help horse owners around the world use the power of the internet and artificial intelligence to find the best sire for their mare.
The platform’s regularly updated AI algorithms and database facilitate both breeding decisions and transactions, allowing users to maximize their horses’ breeding potential.

Aqua tal develops, produces, and markets water treatment systems, providing optimal solutions for filtration and water purification.
Aqua tal continues to expand its operations commercially and technologically with product upgrades and new models released regularly, reflecting the company's intention to innovate and grow. Aqua tal has its headquarters in Israel, and control warehouses, research laboratories, and logistic and administrative offices in Israel, Europe, and the United States. Production and product development take place in China, and products are shipped around the world under the Aqua tal trade name or an OEM.

Yemoja is an innovative microalgae company specializing in industrial production of high-end, microalgae-based biological compounds. Yemoja can grow any algae species according to demand.
Yemoja’s patent-protected Multi Microalgae Advanced Production System is an automated photobioreactor for microalgae cultivation. The system controls the cultivation parameters with an automatic main control system and can preserve the exact cultivation conditions at any scale.

column3:
Desert Labs develops Hoodia parviflora for appetite control. The company preserves the potency of the fresh plant from harvest to manufacturing, and its strains of Hoodia parviflora are pure, safe, and free of agricultural residues.
All of Desert Labs’ products are vegan, gluten-free, and kosher.

ClingTap has developed a one-way spout valve technology that enables various liquids to be dispensed while simultaneously preventing air from entering the container. Its solution extends product shelf life after opening, preserves flavor, and eliminates the need to refrigerate ultra-high-temperature (UHT) processed products after opening, such as UHT milk.
ClingTap’s spout is constructed of two layers of HDPE film that can open under the pressure of liquid passing through it, as well as collapse as a result of the surface tension of the liquid descending inward and away from the spout when pouring is complete. In addition, the spouts are engineered to meet existing pack and fill lines.

Latimeria studies, develops, and operates fish-breeding centers to help meet the world's growing demand for fish. The company has developed a fish-breeding system that is specifically designed to target the biological needs of broodstocks and improve the breeding performance of fish in captivity. It has also developed a recirculation system that suppresses the exchange rates of synthetic seawater.

OogiMe designs cookie cutter models for 3D printing. Customers can choose from various shapes, numbers, and forms, including animals, leaves, balloons, sports items, familiar animated characters, holiday themes, and more.
OogiMe files are available for download through online 3D model publishers, enabling customers to easily download, print, and use the cutters.

ICL is a global manufacturer of products based on specialty minerals primarily in agriculture, food, and engineered materials.
ICL produces approximately a third of the world's bromine and is the sixth-largest potash producer, as well as the leading provider of pure phosphoric acid. It is a major manufacturer of specialty fertilizers, specialty phosphates, and flame retardants. ICL's mining and manufacturing activities are supported by global distribution and supply networks and located in Israel, Europe, the Americas, and China.

column3: Tawodi is developing a solution that uses machine learning algorithms and high-resolution airborne sensors to identify biotic and abiotic stresses with high specificity. The solution is designed to alert farmers to stresses and their location and spread, thereby optimizing inputs, reducing crop losses, and increasing yields.
column11: europe, eastern europe, east asia, china, united states

column3:
WITI Sense specializes in the development of remote sensors for use in the agricultural industry. The company has developed a technology that allows cultivators to instantly inspect and analyze live plants in a nondestructive manner. The company’s first focus is the cannabis plant.
WITI Sense’s electro-optical hardware applies data fusion that combines several technologies, including AI and a learning algorithm. Its remote sensing provides instant data about plant health, including chemical composition and overall quality optimization.
INNOCAKE uses a combination of current technologies, like a 5-axis computer-controlled machine, to create photorealistic cakes based on 3D imaging.

GrowDirector is focused on providing distributors with insights into the world of growers through the use of big data and artificial intelligence. The company leverages its centralized position within the modern, evolving growers’ arena while also creating long-term relationships.

EViation Aircraft is developing and manufacturing efficient electric aircraft in an effort to provide a fast, competitive, and sustainable solution to the on-demand mobility needs of people and goods. With distributed propulsion, high-energy density batteries, mission-driven energy management, and a new airframe designed to maximize these technological advances, EViation aims to make regional transportation more efficient.

PRACTI develops retail systems from mobile point-of-sale apps that are tailored for small retail chains and franchises, allowing them to keep all their data in the cloud while keeping it accessible from anywhere at any time.
The platform also provides in-store sensors to get a better understanding of offline analytics, as well as white-label consumer-facing apps that create a tailored experience for PRACTI's retailers and their customers.

Elisra develops, manufactures, and supplies comprehensive solutions in the electromagnetic spectrum domain, including electronic warfare (EW), spectrum control, communications, and signal intelligence.
The company is a primary source of EW suites for the Israel Air Force and for many other air forces around the world, integrating radar warning receivers (RWR), laser warning systems (LWS), IR missile warning systems (MWS), electronic countermeasures (ECM), and chaff/flare.

hiSky provides a satellite communication network system that enables the provision of robust, low-cost satellite services to large numbers of users, all over the globe. Operating on GEO and LEO satellites, the company's network comprises satellite terminals and hub base stations, a mobile application, IoT/M2M interface, and application servers.
hiSky products are suited to commercial IoT and voice/data, and the system architecture enables a flexible business model, providing either the full service or terminals and hub equipment, depending on customer requirements. All the technology integrated into hiSky products is developed in house, enabling the company to adapt to specific customer requirements and respond quickly to market demands.

column3:
ARTsys360 develops a 3D, 360º micro-radar sensor designed to protect compounds, improve traffic lights in smart cities, and enable autonomous cars. The patented technology allows a reduction in price, weight, and energy consumption compared with similar systems.
The company’s RS360-400 for drone detection is a light, low-cost, compact, and reliable micro-radar system with low energy consumption. The system detects human targets, flying drones, and vehicles within a 360º radius and up to a few hundred meters away.

Aquallence has developed a system for central water purification that harnesses the natural power of ozone oxidation to provide people everywhere with safe and clean water with no chemical interference. Designed for scalability, the company’s system operates across the entire water supply chain, from private residences and water kiosks to schools, buildings, and municipal systems.
Aquallence also offers transportable water purifiers as a solution for first responders, including mobile forces, rescue units, and special missions operating under severe conditions or in disaster-stricken areas. In addition, the company serves rural areas that lack clean water and stable electricity, as well as urban centers with aging water infrastructures vulnerable to sewage and waste contamination.

Mileutis is a bio-pharmaceutical company focused on the discovery, development, and commercialization of novel and biologically sourced, safe, and residual-free therapies for animal and human health.
The company's lead products are Imilac and Milac, which target the management, treatment, and prevention of mastitis in dairy cows.
Mileutis's technology and products consist of peptides and specific protein fragments derived from milk that have a positive impact on conditions that influence health and reduce antibiotic use in animal health management.

Agrosoft develops agricultural software for export-marketing companies, local markets, packing houses, distribution companies, and farms. The company's products facilitate integration between the computer systems of growers and marketing companies, with the aim of getting more rapid and effective control over information and reducing expenses.
Agrosoft's Agropriority software for managing packing houses and marketers of agricultural products is based on the priority enterprise resource planning software of Eshbel Technologies Ltd, with the addition of an agriculture module developed by Agrosoft.

Ambrosia SupHerb produces vitamins, minerals, and dietary supplements. It is currently the only factory in Israel with the technology and capability to manufacture soft-gel capsules.
The company's plant in Upper Nazareth develops, manufactures, markets, and exports SupHerb's brand to private-label customers. Ambrosia SupHerb also imports and markets the Solgar brand.

Westham Innovations is a biotech company that provides solutions for controlling adult mosquitoes and sand flies, which are vectors for a number of diseases, including malaria, dengue, lashmania, and yellow fever.
Westham’s proprietary core technology is Attractant Targeted Sugar Bait (ATSB). The efficacy of ATSB has been demonstrated by numerous field tests and lab experiments worldwide. ATSB-based products are used by PCOs and municipalities in the United States to control nuisance mosquitoes. Its applications include residential and urban use as well as agricultural pest control.

Lishtot is an Israeli technology company dedicated to improving water quality around the world. Using a core technology based on a newly discovered phenomenon associated with electric fields and water, Lishtot develops products that rapidly test drinking water for numerous types of contaminants and then aggregates the information to create a clearer picture of global water quality.
The Lishtot TestDrop is a handheld keychain device that detects contaminants such as E. coli, lead, arsenic, mercury, copper, chlorine, and protein at EPA and WHO standards. The two-second test displays either a blue or a red light to indicate the absence or presence of contaminants. The TestDrop connects via Bluetooth to the Lishtot mobile app, where users can track their test history; view more data on their water, including the likelihood of contamination; and distinguish between bottled water, tap water, and natural water from rivers and streams.

column3:
Anlit manufactures consumer vitamins and minerals as well as dietary supplements intended primarily for children.
The company’s products are natural, with no artificial colors or preservatives, and come in the form of pectin-based gummy bears and chewable, chocolate-textured bears. These delivery formats are market ready for supplement providers, distributors, and retailers and can be extended to other applications.

column3: Unavoo Food Technologies has developed HEYLO, a sweetener made from all-natural ingredients with a glycemic value of zero, no artificial or chemical ingredients, no sugar components, and almost no calories. HEYLO provides a sugar-like taste profile with no aftertaste and has already been successfully implemented in many products including ketchup, peanut butter, dairy products, and flavored water.

Hilico aims to provide off-grid solutions for water, food, energy, and hygiene to impoverished communities in the developing world.
Hilico developed a portable, lightweight rain harvesting system. The device is designed to sustainably provide clean drinking water to off-grid communities and disaster relief areas. The device can be connected to any kind of vertical object like a pole or a tree, with a single clamp, in just a few minutes. Rain falling into the device is funneled via a small filtration unit into a bag where the water can be kept.

Woosh Water Systems provides an end-to-end solution for drinking water for smart cities. The company’s water stations are designed specifically for the urban lifestyle, providing clean, healthy, and affordable water to people on the go.
Each station contains a purification system and a bottle-cleansing system for reusable bottles. Woosh water stations are user-friendly, fully computerized, and remotely monitored by a control center for 24/7 service.

Cooling Quality Management (CQM) develops cost-effective fouling prevention and water treatment systems for cooling systems. The company develops environmentally friendly solutions designed to keep heat exchangers and cooling towers continuously free of scale, organic growth, and corrosion. In most cases, the company's systems totally replace the water chemicals used, save cooling water and energy, and provide a quick return on investment.

column3:
Ukko's mission is to improve the lives of people with food allergies and sensitivities. Ukko uses immunology, machine learning, and protein engineering to make measurably better and safer proteins for use in food and therapeutics. Ukko does this by designing and controlling the molecular interactions between allergen proteins and the immune system.
Ukko's technology uses samples from patients and machine learning to guide the engineering of superior proteins that can be incorporated into food products and therapeutics. These proteins maintain or improve beneficial properties (taste, nutritional value, yield, and physicochemical and mechanical properties) but do not trigger an immune response. Ukko's initial product pipeline includes celiac-safe gluten proteins, allergy-safe and therapeutic peanut proteins, as well as a pipeline of additional allergen proteins.

myAir specializes in personalized plant-based food products for stress management. Using deep profiling based on machine-learning technology, the company has developed nutrition bars designed for long-term stress management routines.

Stern Engineering designs water-conservation products using infrared technology. The company's wide range of products includes electronic wall-mounted and deck-mounted faucets, touch-free soap dispensers, electronic flush valves for urinals and toilets, electronic shower controls, shower panels, and vandal-resistant shower heads. Stern also produces a large variety of components such as infrared sensors, piezo switches, and solenoid valves.

Tairob Industrial Technology has developed the Micro-Foam Milk Maker, which creates uniformly dense and naturally sweet micro-foam milk from cow, goat, or soy milk.
The company's research and development fields include robotic technology and computerized electromechanical machines. Tairob aims to establish a new methodology for making micro-foam milk in coffee bars and at home.

Forrest Innovations is implementing its Natural Vector Control (NVC) solution to control mosquitoes. Harnessing a naturally occurring mechanism (RNAi), the company produces sterile non-GM male mosquitoes and releases them en masse from airplanes to compete with the wild population. Forrest's operational process combines Modular Mobile Mosquito Units for mass production of NVCs and massive aerial release capabilities for efficient mosquito control.
column11: americas, north america, central america, south america, southeast asia, africa, brazil, united states

column3:
Amai Proteins develops and produces protein-based ingredients for everyday applications. Its first innovation uses sweet designer proteins as a substitute for sugar. Combining agile integrative computational protein design (AI-CPD) with biotechnology-based production, Amai creates novel proteins that are healthy, tasty, food-compatible, and cost-effective.
The company’s hypersweet proteins were evaluated in a variety of beverage and dairy applications by top-ten food and beverage multinationals. Its sweeteners were found to have an excellent sensory profile, thermostabliity (for pasteurization), and synergy with other sweeteners.

SunDo is an agricultural community platform that connects farmers and volunteers for substantive, collaborative working experiences designed to have a meaningful social impact. It partners with hundreds of farms throughout the country and offers volunteers a wide range of activities from the farming world, from picking, pruning, and shaping to working with sheep and cattle.
SunDo helps all volunteers find the activity most appropriate to their character, pace, and ability, positioning them to get the most from the valuable and uplifting communal work. In addition to the agricultural tasks, volunteers will also enjoy social activities, local attractions, new friendships, and unforgettable experiences.

Aqualink creates modular filters for a variety of filtration needs, providing tailor-made sets of filters to address specific water-quality issues. The company's systems are equipped with a user-friendly filter replacement mechanism whose simple twist-lock design enables filters to be replaced quickly and easily with no need for additional tools or technicians.
The company also manages an R&D lab for analyzing and developing new filtration solutions.

WATEFY has developed a technology that makes it possible to enrich water with calcium and magnesium bicarbonates to any desired level, enabling the inexpensive industrial production of high-quality bottled and household water.
The company’s technology allows healthy drinking water to be made from desalinated seawater, soft natural water, or poor-quality tap water. It accomplishes this through the addition of vital calcium and magnesium bicarbonates as required by health authorities in accordance with international or national standards, as well as to reduce water corrosivity to prevent water infrastructure deterioration.

MAOLAC's mission is to develop tailored bio-functional ingredients from specific bovine milk proteins that are homologous to human breast milk in order to strengthen and support specific body systems and organs.
MAOLAC uses artificial intelligence and computational biology to capture, enrich, and create tailored active mixtures.

CHKP is engaged in the development of plant-based dairy alternative consumer products based primarily on chickpea protein, including milk for coffee or cereal, drinking yogurt, spoonable yogurt, spreadable cream cheese, and sweet puddings.

Zavitan Technologies developed RightWash, a shower system based on a warm airstream saturated with hot water spray. The company's solution is aiming to save up to 90% of water usage in regular showers.
The company is also working on a product for hand washing.

Brandmark is developing blockchain technology that enables the tracking and testing of batches randomly along the supply chain, thereby providing assurance that products are safe for use and creating a bond of trust between the brand and the consumer.
Brandmark is a joint venture between Emurgo, a global blockchain solutions provider, and Blackbird, an Israeli-based venture capital and private equity firm.

NewRocket is developing proprietary gel technology that enables a stable and non-toxic engine propellant, without sacrificing performance or control. NewRocket's gel propellant combines the advantages of liquid and solid propellants. Safe to use and transport, the propellant will improve rocket performance, offering a powerful thrust that can be controlled and extinguished when needed. NewRocket's gel propulsion technology is designed to meet the strictest industry regulations.

Synergio is focused on reshaping the consumer goods industry with smart ingredients for healthier, sustainable products. The company’s patented micro-targeting technology enables all-natural ingredients to achieve the desired effects without side effects.
Using a data-driven computational platform, Synergio is leveraging a deep understanding of plants in order to accelerate health and sustainability worldwide.

PDT Agro uses pulse detonation technology (PDT) to create shock waves that can be used for a variety of applications. The company is developing solutions for the agricultural sector, including an environmentally friendly bird-control system and a soil-disinfection machine.
The technology takes advantage of the gas dynamics and thermodynamic processes associated with detonative combustion. Rapid combustion is created via a detonation wave produced by a premixed fuel/oxidizer mixture. The system’s detonation process is designed to be well controlled, reliable, and economical.

AIRLIFT One is the developer of an efficient, all-electric vertical take-off and landing (eVTOL) air taxi designed to transport two to five people at speeds five times faster than a car.
Using eVTOL technology, AIRLIFT One aims to enable users to access city centers via aircraft, transforming a previously stressful commute into a thrilling ride with its point-to-point, on-demand, and autonomous high-capacity transport system.

iPIPE is developing a system that autonomously performs visual, audio, electro-magnetic, and ultrasonic inspection of active water pipe networks. The system inspects from inside the pipes, providing valuable operational information regarding pipe corrosion before pipe rupture, pirate connections, and other hazardous malfunctions developing inside the pipes.
iPIPE's technology provides a complete network survey, pinpointing the exact location of existing or developing malfunctions, facilitating efficient, cost-effective maintenance of the water network.

Urban Aeronautics (UA) has developed advanced aerodynamic technologies that are the basis for a family of internal rotor (ducted fan) aircraft known as Fancraft. UrbanAero capitalizes on its portfolio of intellectual property via two subsidiary companies, each of which is developing unique Fancraft for specific markets.
Tactical Robotics was formed in order to focus on the development of air vehicle configurations based on a license from UA for the unmanned military and homeland security markets. The Cormorant (formerly AirMule) is an advanced and patented vertical-takeoff-and-landing unmanned air vehicle. The Cormorant utilizes internal lift rotors that enable it to fly inside obstructed (e.g. mountainous, wooded, or urban) terrain where helicopters are unable to operate.

M.D.S Wireless Technologies designs complete, on-demand, custom online switches and devices as “mini smart home” options. The company is the developer of the Smart Switch, a boiler-control platform using patented, advanced Wi-Fi technology.
The Smart Switch pairs through Wi-Fi with Switcher, a smartphone app that allows users to control their home’s boiler from their phones. Users can define a daily and weekly schedule and can also evaluate their electric energy consumption history.

column3:
VAYU Sense develops bio-fermentation solutions through the use of artificial intelligence and digital services, with a focus on yield increase, turnover optimization, process robustness, process duration, and early contamination detection.
The company’s customizable solution controls the fermentation process in real time by automatically updating production control parameters such as feeding, agitation, and gas flow. Results include better process control, higher yield, and optimized capacity utilization.

Nuversys is focused on the development omega-3 microcapsules for use in food. Based on a proprietary micro delivery balls (MDB) technology, the company’s products are designed to overcome the traditional constraints against using omega-3s in food, including odor, oxidation, and reduced potency.
Nuversys has completed a proof of concept and is currently optimizing the product for stability and efficacy, after which its omega-3 MDBs will be used as raw materials in energy bars and other foods.

Incredibowl develops and produces edible tableware products. The company's goal is to raise environmental awareness and reduce disposable plastic usage by providing tasty, appealing, and fun alternatives in the form of edible tableware. The company is developing products like edible shot glasses, salty bowls, and sweet bowls.

Memotree is an eco-solutions company that produces biological servers that store encrypted information inside trees, plants, and seeds. Memotree creates trees, plants, and seeds that carry the data without the need for electricity. The data is safely protected and can be retrieved any time. The company's products include living memorial trees, "disks on trees," and DNA preservation.

Bluvstein Binot Topaz specializes in providing water and wastewater treatment systems for industrial and municipal applications. Its tailor-made, technology-based systems are designed to provide efficiency, effectiveness, and reliability.

Seakura is a producer of "super seaweed," offering a wide range of seaweed products to retail and food companies worldwide. The company cultivates and adds value to some of the finest and cleanest seaweed in the world.
Seakura combines proprietary aquaculture technology in land-based eco-pools, free from open-sea pollution, with multi-crop, organic, sustainable methods to enable farmers around the world to locally grow and supply a variety of fresh, clean, and highly nutritional seaweed year-round, regardless of sea or weather conditions.

Polysack produces sustainable films, while utilizing machine direction orientation technology. The company's films are suitable for numerous applications including high-shrink labels, candy wrappers, and a variety of bags and pouches. Polysack provides a line of solutions to converters and other third parties in the food and beverage industry.
Polysack brands include Polyphane Pack 'n Cycle, which are green films for the production of bags, pouches, and sachets; Polyphane FIT, which is high-shrink polyolefin-based film used for producing flexible, wraparound shrink labels; and Polyphane TWIST, which is a film for wrapping candies, chocolates, and sweets.

VBact develops and manufactures automated real-time systems for the detection and enumeration of bacteria and foreign microparticles in water. Its solutions are designed to provide revolutionary microbial industrial automation and Industry 4.0 capabilities.
The company’s continuous in-line technology is based on an innovative direct-imaging method; advanced proprietary image-processing algorithms, including ML/AI; and liquid management techniques. The technology is uniquely free from labeling, culture methods, and the use of biochemistry reagents.

column3: Tavlit supplies irrigation products to international companies in the water and irrigation industry and DIY chains in more than 70 countries. Its products include plastic filters, valves, connectors, and irrigation emitters such as foggers and micro sprinklers.

column3: Yamit creates purification systems for the industrial, municipal, and agriculture markets. The company's water treatment filters are based on its media, screen, and sand separation technologies, which protect systems by removing solids that may clog or contaminate water passages.

Tama Group has developed and patented netting products to secure goods that need air circulation onto pallets. Tama also designs and manufactures housewares and garden ornaments.
The company's products include round-bale net wraps for crop packaging; pallet-wrapping nets; reinforcement nets; twine for round bales; plastic slats for poultry flooring; benches and bench tops for nurseries and garden centers; and shade nets for protection against solar radiation, frost, wind, hail, and birds.

UET is an engineering and manufacturing company that develops solutions for treating water without chemical additives.
UET’s water treatment systems use the natural attributes of water to fix the costly problems that it causes, including scaling, heavy metal buildup, corrosion, and biocontamination. Its solutions are easy to install and maintain, and have been shown to reduce maintenance and water costs.

Etgar designs, develops, and supplies harvesting tools and equipment that respond to the needs of specific crops.
Etgar’s tools are designed for easy operation and maintenance, and can be adapted easily to any type of crop, soil, or environmental condition to ensure that produce is not damaged or wasted during the harvesting process.

Plastopil develops, manufactures, and markets flexible barrier films and technologically advanced packaging solutions designed to optimize the shelf life and presentation of chilled foods. The company's products include down-gauged barrier films for lidding, better-forming barrier films for tubular form fill seal systems, unique barrier pouches, and highly flex-resistant barrier films.

Magen eco-Energy specializes in the R&D, production, and marketing of solar swimming pool heating solutions, swimming pool water treatment systems, and corrosive-resistant heat exchangers. The company's heat exchangers are designed and built to operate for long periods in corrosive environments of inorganic acids, brines, and alkaline fluids in the metal finishing, semiconductor, chemical, and agricultural industries.

Else Nutrition is an Israel-based food and nutrition company focused on developing innovative, clean, and plant-based food and nutrition products for infants, toddlers, children, and adults. Its plant-based, non-soy formula is a clean-ingredient alternative to dairy-based formula.
Else Nutrition (formerly INDI) won the "2017 Best Health and Diet Solutions" award at the Global Food Innovation Summit in Milan.

Eatsane develops proprietary formulations and technology for creating foods that are both low in carbs and low on the glycemic index, including chocolate pralines, bread, and ice cream.
The company’s products are made with wholesome ingredients, remain very similar to their original versions, and provide increased nutritional value while maintaining compatibility with standard industrial manufacturing methods.

Zero Egg has developed a nutritious plant-based liquid egg that tastes, looks, and functions like a real egg and can be used as an egg substitute in any recipe, including omelets, baked goods, mayonnaise, and sauces. Zero Egg has a high nutritional value and no cholesterol.
In 2019, Zero Egg won the Foodtech Innovation Competition held at Calcalit's FoodTech conference.

column3:
LightCann develops solid-state LED lights designed for indoor cannabis growing. The lights have high light intensity and purity while maintaining low power consumption. The LightCann lights are more than 95% efficient and driven by power supplies that operate in current mode; therefore, the overall energy consumption is translated to light output rather than heat.
LightCann's products, including the LightCann 72 and LightCann 36s Super Compact, are optimized for maximal light output while responding to the needs of the plants in both vegging and flowering stages.

LIVEgg is a biotech company that develops solutions for the poultry industry. The company is the creator of the CrystalEgg, an embryo-monitoring system that provides hatchery management teams with real-time knowledge regarding the development stage and condition of the embryos within the incubator.
The company is also developing the ChickMale Saver, which is a noninvasive sex-identification system for poultry embryos. In addition to its primary benefit of preventing the unnecessary killing of day-old male chicks, the ChickMale Saver will eliminate the need for the manual chick-sorting process.

Amarlane Foods produces natural foods designed to make healthy food products available to everyone. Amarlane is the creator of Betterine, a substitute for butter and margarine made from four natural ingredients. The company also has other natural products in various stages of development.
column11: europe, australia, belgium, canada, france, israel, mexico, united kingdom, united states

column3: Pigmentum developed a molecular mechanism that enables external gene activation in plants (beginning with pigment changes and designs). The company has a patent on the inducible activation of pigment production abilities. The company will use its technology for high-scale production of natural compounds for the food, pharmaceutical, and cosmetic industries.

Yo-Egg is developing a plant-based egg substitute designed for consumers who wish to enjoy a sunny-side-up egg without harming animals or the planet and without having to compromise on appearance, flavor, texture, or nutritional value.
The company’s egg substitute can be incorporated into a wide variety of dishes across multiple cuisines and styles. In addition, the plant-based product is free of both cholesterol and egg-associated pathogens such as salmonella.

TRCKD is an IoT supply chain tracking solution with an all-in-one visualized business intelligence platform. TRCKD turns every asset into a smart asset, which can allow supply chain managers to match supply and demand, improve shelf life, and reduce food waste.

Miya was established by Shari Arison as part of Arison Investments with the vision of ensuring an abundance of fresh water through the efficient management of cities’ existing fresh water resources.
The company seeks to optimize the water supply in urban water systems worldwide. It partners with utilities to design and implement comprehensive, technology-based solutions that can improve the client’s financial and operational efficiency while also enhancing customer service levels, reducing energy consumption, and lowering contamination and health risks in order to benefit people, the community, and the environment.

Odis Filtering designs, manufactures, installs, and commissions water and wastewater treatment plants. Its custom-made solutions consider the technical and economic needs of each customer to provide the most efficient solution. The company creates solutions for wastewater treatment, drinking water, industrial process water, emergency and relief water, and greywater recycling.
Odis is active in the international market through its subsidiary companies, distributors, and representatives.

column3:
RT designs, develops, and manufactures the Skystar family of aerostats (lighter-than-air aircraft) for use in intelligence, surveillance, reconnaissance, and communications applications. Skystar products are designed for users in prevent-prepare-respond-recover settings who require continuous and compact aerial support.
RT delivers a self-contained, versatile, easily transportable, cost-effective tactical system that consists of a mobile control station, ground system module, tether, lighter-than-air platform, stabilized payload platform, and sophisticated sensor suite. Skystar systems are easy to operate, rapidly deployed, and customized for a range of operating conditions worldwide in various military and civilian missions.

W-Cycle is a biotechnology company that specializes in pulp packaging solutions for the food service industry. The company offers a line of recyclable, compostable, and disposable products made from bagasse, the fiber pulp of sugarcane stalks that remains after the juice has been extracted.
W-Cycle produces lids, plates, trays, and more. Its products are biodegradable, nontoxic, and can be used in ovens and microwaves at temperatures up to 270 degrees Celsius (430 degrees Fahrenheit) and in freezers as low as -40 degrees Celsius (-40 degrees Fahrenheit).

E.P.C. is a provider of onsite wastewater treatment plants. Its systems serve commercial, public, and residential needs with products based on a proprietary process for air-positive biological reduction.
The company’s two main products are the Bio-Robi, designed for individual homes, and the BioDisk, intended for clusters of residences and small villages. The Bio-Robi is an environmentally friendly wastewater solution that converts domestic sewage into clean, odorless effluent for reuse in irrigation or other applications.

GES is an international leader in the design and construction of innovative sea water desalination and industrial and municipal water and wastewater treatment plants, as well as in the field of chemical production for industrial applications.
GES is owned by Granite HaCarmel, an industrial holding company operating in the energy, water, and construction materials sectors.

Avisco is a biotechnology company introducing Inula viscosa from the wild for cultivation as a standardized crop. The company specializes in Inula viscosa cultivation, processing, extraction, production, standardization, and quality control for a wide range of proprietary herbal therapeutic and skincare formulations.
Avisco holds patents for its technology and products such as AIVOREX, a standardized Inula viscosa oleo resin extract, as well as the intellectual property rights to unpublished studies and Inula viscosa extract applications.

Krausz Industries manufactures pipe-joining and repair devices, including the HYMAX coupling, for use in the water and sewage market sectors. The company’s solutions are designed to be durable and minimize installation time.
Krausz products are used worldwide, with more than one million installations in the United States. The company holds more than 100 international patents for a range of water piping repair and coupling solutions.

Ofra Aqua Plants develops solutions in the fields of water ecology, aquatic plants, and phytotechnologies. The company specializes in different implementations of phytoremediation, such as constructed wetlands and decorative ponds, for wastewater, river and lake management, public ponds, polluted wells, industry and agriculture, and the purification of water for swimming pools.
Ofra Aqua Plants has designed and built constructed wetlands for municipal wastewater treatment, gas stations, military facilities, dairy farms, slaughterhouses, fish farms, landfill leachates, cosmetic factories, and river rehabilitation projects. The company has its own aquatic plant nurseries and a research site, and is designing soil treatment projects to contribute to the environment and wildlife.

BioBee Sde Eliyahu specializes in biologically integrated pest management (IPM), providing farmers with beneficial predatory insects and mites as an alternative to harsh chemical pesticides. The company also offers professional field services to better implement their tailor-made IPM programs.
BioBee produces Phytoseiulus persimilis, an effective natural predator of Tetranychus urticae, the red spider mite. The company also produces and provides bumblebees for natural pollination in greenhouses and open fields.

column3: Hop Engineering develops, manufactures, and markets water improvement systems. The company’s leading product is the PTH water improver, designed for efficient prevention and elimination of scale and rust in cold and hot water systems. The PTH is a low-maintenance device that runs without electricity or the need for chemical additives. The device is suitable for domestic, industrial, and agricultural use.

BioDalia is a manufacturer of biopesticides and fermentation-based products. The company manufactures and markets bioinsecticides for pest management in agriculture and forestry, as well as biolarvicides to control mosquito larvae and fungus gnats.
BioDalia is active in the contract manufacturing of biochemicals by fermentation, industrial bioprocess development, and R&D, and it is Israel’s leading supplier of industrial-scale, multipurpose contract fermentation services.

column3:
Metzer Group is a kibbutz-based manufacturer of micro-irrigation products and various types of pipelines. The Metzer projects department also has expertise in agricultural and irrigation turnkey projects for greenhouses and open fields.
Among the company’s products are SP pipes for cold and hot water plumbing and PE pipes for water infrastructure and telecommunications. Its unique drippers are designed with the widest dripper inlet filter and an innovative pressure-compensating mechanism for precise irrigation and clog-resistance with low-quality water.

Silo is the developer of a vacuum-sealing container system that combines its patented one-touch vacuum technology with an IoT infrastructure designed to help foods stay fresh longer.
Silo’s Alexa Built-in infrastructure offers a solution for tagging and tracking containers’ contents, providing users with around-the-clock access to their kitchen’s inventory and enabling them to know how long their food will be good and when groceries will need to be reordered.

AMI Tens produces tensiometers, soil water samplers, and a variety of accessories for monitoring moisture, fertilizers, and salinity in the soil. The company's product line is based on a porous ceramic cap specifically designed for absorbing soil moisture.

NextFerm develops and produces active ingredients for the food industry. Its products are based on a combination of intellectual property and proprietary know-how in areas including non-GMO technologies and methodologies for enhancing specific characteristics of yeast strains isolated from nature; downstream processing, purification, extraction, and formulation; and clinical research and regulatory work.
The company is currently producing natural astaxanthin from yeast fermentation for human nutrition, implementing its yeast strain improvement technology on a strain that naturally expresses astaxanthin in order to make it a better source. Coupled with downstream engineering and clinical work, this technology results in a product with higher potency, improved flowability, and no odor or flavor in either liquid or powder form.

SION artificially inseminates and breeds dairy cows. The company's breeding program creates a productive Holstein cow that is small and efficient with longevity, persistence, and fertility. The breed has been successful in suboptimal climates around the world.
The company's services include supplying high-quality bull semen, genetic consultation, recommendations for breeding procedures, courses and training sessions on artificial insemination skills, and a variety of other professional services.

Kiinns is a food-safety startup at the intersection of Foodtech and Industry 4.0. The company has developed a technology that completely eliminates food production line cleaning processes, which are both a source of foodborne illnesses and a huge environmental impact.
Kiinns’ technology is designed to prevent foodborne illnesses, save lives, and make the environment cleaner and safer while also dramatically cutting costs for food producers.

Fischer Planning is the developer of SteriVent, a sterile air filtration system that protects storage tanks and other products from airborne contaminants. SteriVent can be used in storage tanks for dairy products, soy milk, juice, cosmetics, pharmaceuticals, and more. The system aims to provide longer product shelf life, clean-in-place benefits, increased cleanliness, and lower energy costs.
In addition, Fischer Planning offers planning, consulting, design, and turnkey systems for aseptic and ultra-clean processing of foods, beverages, cosmetics, and pharmaceuticals. The company also provides design and construction services for new lines in order to improve existing systems through more efficient technologies.

Leaf is a plug-and-plant system that automatically grows medicinal plants and food. The system is designed to automate the growth process and help users save money on medicinal plants. Leaf requires no prior knowledge and can be controlled remotely with the user’s smartphone.
Leaf is developed by Greeley Foodtech, formerly Corsica Innovations.

Rimi develops pest-control products designed to protect plants and the environment. The company’s solutions are designed to control pests and safeguard public health through the use of low-toxicity pesticides for agricultural and animal health applications.
SpareEat connects merchants (restaurants, hotels, grocers, etc.) with consumers to allow them to buy unsold products at reduced prices. The company aims to combat food waste in Israel.

AseptoRay has developed an eco-friendly cold pasteurization method based on ultraviolet technology. Unlike standard thermal pasteurization methods, AseptoRay's process uses ambient temperatures, reducing the impact on nutritional values and eliminating spores and heat-resistant molds. Its technology is designed to increase food safety, quality, and shelf life, while using less energy.
AseptoRay is part of the MGT Group.

AutoAgronom has developed a sustainable precision-agriculture solution that enables growers to save up to 50% in water and up to 70% in fertilizer while increasing yields by as much as 30%.
The company's Root Sense technology "listens" to the plants, analyzes their needs in real time, and automatically delivers water and fertilizer, providing optimal growth conditions throughout the growing cycle.

ShneorSeed develops vegetable seeds that are resistant to a wide range of viruses while also offering high yields and a long shelf life.
The company combines genetics, horticulture, and biology with traditional breeding methods. Its tomato breeds and sweet pepper hybrids have some of the most extensive ranges of virus resistance currently available on the commercial market.

Future Tense develops, produces, and licenses a wide range of fertilizers, pesticides, and other products that are both potent and environmentally acceptable.
Future Tense products, such as Ductil-D, Dentamet, Bio-D, and AZN, are designed to nourish, protect, and enhance crop production. The company also has several products in various stages of development, including ecological soil disinfectants and pesticides, organic chelates, and micronutrient fertilizers.

Anglebase has developed a container for detached substrate cultivation and a system designed to control irrigation and fertilization based on each plant’s specific needs.
With the Anglebase system, a feeding funnel leads drippings directly to the plant’s roots, enabling fertilization and the introduction of organic and other materials straight to the area of consumption while eliminating evaporation and germination of herbs.

Yung-Etgar Agricultural Machinery develops customized products for mechanized harvesting designed to meet the specific needs of each crop. Its focus is obtaining maximum crop recovery with minimal loss.
Each harvesting head is customized to accommodate the particular characteristics of each vegetable, ensuring that delicate produce is not damaged during the process. The heads, designed for easy operation and maintenance, can be adapted to any kind of soil or weather. The system is suitable for tomatoes, peas, corn, beans, paprika, parsley, herbs, broccoli, cauliflower, sweet potatoes, and onions.

Degania Sprayers develops and manufactures sprayers for crops and sanitation. The company invented the Sleeve Boom sprayer, and its latest development is the Double-Row Sleeve Boom sprayer for vineyards, which is designed to control pests and save time and chemicals.
Degania's products are used worldwide by farmers to treat orchards, row crops, cotton fields, citrus groves, and flowers; by hospitals and municipalities for sanitation purposes; and by cattle farmers to spray cow sheds.

Biovac develops and produces vaccines and pharmaceuticals to prevent and treat animal diseases. The company also produces vitamin preparations, disinfectants, and pest-control products.
Biovac invests heavily in research and development, and owns its own production laboratories, including a BSL3 laboratory and a Beta Lactam production alignment. Its production units are authorized and supervised by the Israeli Ministry of Health and Ministry of Agriculture.

column3:
AGM Communication & Control is a provider of smart communication and control solutions for SCADA and DCS systems in the areas of water and wastewater, oil and gas, energy, and environmental real-time monitoring and control.
The company’s original product, R-Win, enables smart, gradual, and economical SCADA/DCS network optimization and upgrading. R-Win, which is installed at remote field stations between the PLC/RTU and the wireless transceiver, is designed to make each station smarter.

miRobot is an add-on robotic solution that automates the complete milking procedure and integrates with existing milking systems to bring full automation to the milking parlor.
The miRobot technology allows farmers to milk multiple stalls simultaneously, with only one supervisor overseeing the whole parlor. This can help reduce labor costs; shorten milking sessions; increase parlor capacity; and improve milk quality, yield, and cow health.

Polyam (Pollination Services Yad-Mordechai) mass-produces bumblebee colonies for pollinating agricultural crops, as well as other beneficial insects for the biological control of greenhouse crop pests.
Polyam produces and markets the predatory bug orius laevigatus, to control thrips in greenhouse sweet peppers and other crops, and the parasitic wasp aphidius colemany for use against aphids.

Raz Sprayers develops and produces agricultural sprayers, with a focus on low-volume machines that provide multi-crop, multi-terrain coverage.
The company’s sprayers can be adjusted for use in vineyards, orchards, and greenhouses, or for open field production of vegetables and flowers. Its product line includes spray heads designed to be replaced quickly and easily.

Paskal Group develops irrigation and growth-monitoring solutions, enabling growers to track and monitor the conditions in which their crop is cultivated, preventing resource spoilage, supporting sustainable growth, increasing yields, and improving quality.
The company's DrainVision product allows growers to control, adjust, and optimize the plant roots' growth. Another of Paskal's products is PhytoVision, which enables farmers to monitor plants' growth rate in the greenhouse; observe growth patterns and their correlation with the climate/irrigation data; compare the performance of different compartments, rows, posts, varieties, and technologies; and more.

The AGAR technology combines a fully open and protected biomass carrier with an efficient aeration and mixing design in various aerobic (e.g. AGAR MBBR and AGAR IFAS) and anaerobic (e.g. DACS and DACS DANA) process configurations, resulting in effective surface areas for biomass growth and oxygen transfer efficiency.
