Desalitech is a provider of high-recovery water production and effluent treatment solutions. The company’s ReFlex reverse osmosis (RO) systems offer maximum recovery and feature Desalitech’s patented closed-circuit desalination (CCD) process.
CCD represents an improvement in RO water treatment by achieving efficient use of water resources, reduced emission of brine waste, increased flexibility and reliability, and lower power consumption, all using standard, off-the-shelf RO components.

StePac develops and manufactures high-quality, precision-engineered modified atmosphere/modified humidity (MA/MH) packaging for fresh produce. Tailor-made for each specific type of vegetable, fruit, or herb, StePac ensures an extended shelf life while maintaining the freshness, flavor, and nutritional value of produce.
The polymers of the company’s Xtend MA/MH packaging are engineered to allow the produce inside the bag to equilibrate within the specific range of O2 and CO2 concentrations required by the particular fruit or vegetable. Xtend slows senescence (aging), maintains the nutritional value and flavor of produce, reduces decay, preserves firmness, and prevents shriveling.

R-Jet Engineering is the developer of the Orbiting Combustion Nozzle (OCN) gas turbine engine. The OCN rotates the air and hot gases in the combustor with the compressor and turbine, eliminating the need for two sets of static blades. As a result, an OCN engine can be built at half the size of a conventional jet of similar power, with fewer components and at a lower cost.
In addition, the OCN engine uses at least 25% less fuel than conventional engines, and its emissions of carbon dioxide and nitrogen oxide can be cut by three-quarters because of its ignition properties.

Magic Technologies manufactures and markets water-saving products for showers, faucets, and waterless urinals. The company produces Green-P waterless urinals, which are designed to contribute to the quality of the environment, promote washroom hygiene, and provide cost savings.
Magic Technologies is part of Magic Ceramic, which was awarded a Green Globe Award.

Raanan Fish Feed develops aquaculture feed based on extruded fish feed, crumbled starter feeds, and organic fish feed.
The company’s products address a wide range of nutritional needs and provide balanced and complete feeding programs.

Sensilize combines smart image analysis with UAS technology to provide up-to-date agronomic information to agribusinesses. The company's user-friendly spatial decision-support system uses imagery to provide thorough information about vegetation.
The system is based on an autonomous UAS outfitted with Sensilize's Robin, which is composed of lightweight commercial multispectral sensors. The gathered data is rapidly processed in the cloud using Sensilize's expert interpretation services.

Farm Dog offers a pest and disease management platform designed to help growers optimize their field treatments, increase yields, and promote environmental sustainability. The company’s solution aims to ensure that fields receive the right treatment, at the right time and location, via AI-enabled workflow software and analytics.
The Farm Dog app enables users to track pests, diseases, weeds, trap counts, and more. It provides georeferencing and photographic findings; logs field visits and sets reminders for special checkups; reminds farmers to return to past hotspots and visit neglected areas; and sends external reports directly from the field.

VGI produces organic fertilizers from natural components that support healthy, natural plant growth. Its products reduce carbon dioxide emissions in agricultural production and help break the cycle of excess chemical use in agriculture.
VGI’s product lines include the KF formulation for home gardening or agriculture, which is designed to enhance crop size, weight, color, and yield. It is nontoxic to humans, nonpolluting, and does not scorch leaves. The product can be applied through irrigation systems or as a foliar spray or soil drench.

Elgressy Engineering Services develops and markets comprehensive solutions and systems for treating and preventing common water-related problems including scale, bacteria, and corrosion. The company’s main product, the AQIN-1, is used in thousands of locations both in Israel and overseas. It uses a combination of a magnetic field with advanced filtering technology to successfully remove iron, manganese, arsenic, sand, and corrosion particles from the water. The product is chemical-free, low-maintenance, and energy efficient.

Triteia uses granular chlorine, which has a higher and more stable concentration of active chlorine, is involved in lower transportation and storage costs, and has fewer environmental and safety risks. WeedOUT is the developer of a proprietary product made with natural ingredients for the eradication of resistant weeds. The company’s goal is to reduce the need for toxic herbicides and higher herbicide doses.
WeedOUT’s technology is based on the development of a special weed pollen, applied via artificial pollination, that leads to weed seed abortion, effectively blocking the next generation of viable weed seeds.

indorz seeks to bring data analytics, prediction, and automation to enterprise cannabis farming. The company’s sensor technology provides farmers with a full dashboard array of key data points, critical alerts, and predictive maintenance algorithms to optimize crop production operations.
The indorz software/hardware command-and-control solution analyzes key data during the growing process while receiving inputs from three sensors: an atmospheric sensor, which collects the climate values of the facility; a water reservoir sensor, which monitors the water supply; and a plant media sensor, which tracks the structure and health of the plants.

BiomicAgritech developed a method for growing vegetables in tubes that can be rotated, which enables the vegetables to grow from the top down, so trellising is done by gravity. This vegetable growing technology helps reduce the need for manual trellising.

The company’s strategic focus is renewable woody biomass, with plantation forestry, biopower (pellets for combustion and co-firing), and biofuels (cellulose to ethanol) as its target sectors. The company’s platform organizes information and documents from the first stage in the chain of production (parent flocks) through the sale of meat products and table eggs. The company's solution, which is offered as a service to farmers and agronomists, can reduce the time to analysis to between 10 and 60 minutes using a compact mobile laboratory that automatically prepares samples and analyzes component material elements.
Croptimal's technology utilizes multispectral spectroscopy and electrical measurement units for a full range of material analysis of nutrients and contaminants. It includes fast, accurate measurement of nitrogen, phosphorous, and potassium, as well as microelements such as iron, magnesium, manganese, and zinc in all forms and at set intervals.

iShence is developing a system for growers that could help them rapidly achieve great yields. This modular system has various sensor capabilities and the ability to monitor and control many grow aspects. It is cloud based, intelligent, and easy to operate.
The system enables light wavelength control depending on growth stage, via image processing. It also contains a runoff sensor for precise irrigation and nutrient adjustment, and it is composed of a wide set of sensors connected to a single controller.

Milkit has developed a milk dispensing system consisting of a large, durable, tear-resistant milk bag connected to an electric tap. The company’s system provides a clean, economical, and environmentally friendly milk dispensing solution for the food service industry.

WaterComms is developing software tools to integrate services, products, and technologies into a functioning, quasi-centralized water sector that restores trust and enjoys economy-of-scale effects through better data production, traction, and management.

Israel Aerospace Industries (IAI) is an aerospace and defense company developing technologies in space, air, land, naval, cyber, and homeland security for defense and commercial markets.
IAI provides customers with tailor-made solutions to the unique challenges they face including satellites, unmanned aerial vehicles, missiles, intelligence solutions, weapon systems, air defense systems, robotic systems, radars, business jets, aero-structures, and more.

Agrimor provides formulations of agricultural pesticides in all forms, concentrations, and private-label mixtures, as well as technical-grade materials.
The company’s products include fungicides, herbicides, insecticides acaricides, technical materials, veterinary products, organic products, and spray oils.

Agrematch is a pioneering data-science product discovery and development company for novel bioactive compounds and the access point for compound-based in silico discovery. Agrematch caters to industries including human and animal health, food production, and agriculture. The company’s initial focus is on the discovery of compounds that possess both the desired activity and a high potential to become sustainable agricultural products.

Flytrex Aviation offers tailored, end-to-end drone delivery solutions based on its proprietary cloud technology. The company supplies its Mule drone as part of a complete solution. The Mule is made of carbon fiber and can carry a three-kilogram load and travel up to 13 kilometers at a speed of up to 55 kilometers/hour.
Flytrex also develops live black boxes for multirotors and quadcopters. The Flytrex Live 3G is a black box for personal drones that transmits its current location via a 3G cellular network in real time. The company's network spans 15,000 of its black boxes and 90 countries.

AGRIDERA Seeds & Agriculture breeds, produces, and sells open-field crops, vegetables, and flower seeds. The company's seed activity focuses on open-field crop seeds including wheat, confection watermelon, and clover; vegetable seeds such as tomatoes and eggplants; and ornamental seeds like hybrid cut sunflowers.
AGRIDERA maintains agricultural and genetic research in cooperation with the Weizmann Institute, Volcani Institute, and Hebrew University. The company split from Zeraim Gedera in 2000 and has continued to provide it and other agriculture companies with crop-management services.

GNE Global Natural Energy grows algae for green fuel, human consumption, and animal feed.
GNE has developed modular system to grow and harvest algae on a commercial level. It supplies turnkey projects for growing algae; separating algae biomass; drying algae for commercial use; and extracting oil for bio-diesel.
The company operates as a subsidiary of World Health Energy Holdings, Inc.

Beeologics LLC is dedicated to restoring bee health and protecting the future of honey bee pollination.
Beeologics is developing a line of RNAi-based products to specifically address the long-term well being of honey bees, including the control of parasites and how they’re involved in Colony Collapse Disorder (CCD).
Beeologics was acquired by Monsanto Company in 2011.

GrowHome is a leading supplier of hydroponics equipment online, through mail order, and in a national chain of shops. The company offers smart solutions and quality controls for growing cannabis plants using advanced LED grow-light systems.
GrowHome is dedicated to offering an exceptional range of hydroponics products and providing expert advice to the hydroponics and indoor gardening community.

IrriPass develops devices that facilitate mobile drip irrigation lines and bridge the gap between drip and traditional furrow irrigation. The devices are based on a scroll and deployment concept for tree plantations and a lateral shifting concept for row crops, and allow irrigation of several plots with the same set of drip lines.

Geshem Genomics has developed a computational platform to evaluate plant genomic data and identify traits with agronomic importance.
Using the company's computational genomics technology, breeders do not have to wait for plants to mature to observe the traits of new varieties of fruits and vegetables. Based on genomic data taken from leaves at an early development stage, breeders can find out much sooner which plants will have desired trait combination at maturity, and significantly reduce the cost of their trials.

WeCookit, developed by Mango Tree Ltd,  is an interactive cooking platform that connects kids with the food they eat.
The majority of the editorial content is based on fresh, healthy products, but WeCookit believes children should be exposed to a variety of foods, ingredients and cooking techniques. Therefore, there also are recipes that include not-so-healthy ingredients such as chocolate.

Xmatch Genetics improves existing herd genetics and specialized breeding programs to help customers improve their bottom line, while at the same time looking out for animal welfare and increasing and securing ample global food supply.

Hazera is an active player in the global seed industry, with a focus on breeding, developing, and producing a variety of vegetable seeds.
The company is dedicated to cultivating progress through dedicated research, combining modern science with traditional breeding methods to create high-quality, high-yielding varieties.
Hazera’s data-driven breeding, based on genomics and phenomics technology, is designed to provide customers with tailored varieties featuring an innovative set of traits.

CultiVu aims to improve small farm productivity by connecting farmers with local agricultural advisors. Using the company's free platform, farmers can receive relevant, insightful, reliable instructions and knowledge from local advisers to improve productivity and reduce costs and risks.
Public and private sector institutions can use the data created by the CultiVu platform to better understand trends in farming and agriculture across regions and crops.

column3:
Natratec develops and manufactures organic protective emulsions for post-harvest agricultural products and the poultry industry. The company’s two main applications, NatraLife and NatraHatch, are designed to retain the freshness of fruits and vegetables and increase the egg-hatching rate of poultry, respectively.
Acting as a fully organic membrane, NatraLife effectively regulates respiration while, at the same time, preventing the evaporation of much-needed moisture. With NatraLife, the natural ripening process of fruits and vegetables is dramatically slowed, weight loss is significantly reduced, and the development of decay, dryness, and fermentation is delayed.
column11: australia, mexico, spain, united kingdom, united states

column3:
Rosetta Green develops improved plant traits for the agriculture and biofuel industries using unique genes called microRNAs. The company identifies and uses these genes to control key processes in major crops such as corn, wheat, rice, soybean, cotton, canola, and algae.
Combining computational biology, molecular biology, plant tissue culture, plant transformation, and high throughput trait screening, Rosetta Green identifes the most promising microRNAs that could potentially be used to improve key plant traits in major crops.

Profiline Industries manufactures greenhouses for clients around the world. The company produces all of the necessary parts for its greenhouses, including tubing and pipes, at its production facility in Israel. Profiline’s products can also be used for fish farms.

CommonSensor offers the CommonSensor, a wireless device that allows plants to essentially water themselves, saving up to 75% in water consumption and proportionally reducing the pollution of both water and soil caused by fertilizers.
The CommonSensor constantly monitors the amount of water in the ground and opens the irrigation valve when the amount falls below a preassigned watering threshold level. When the water reaches the desired level, the system closes the valve.

Morflora has developed a bio-based, generic, non-transgenic trait-introduction solution that protects plants and seeds from a wide variety of diseases. The company’s solution also introduces desirable traits for crop enhancement, including improved yield, quality, and functionality.
The company’s TraitUP method immediately expresses in plants without causing genetic modification or affecting successive generations. TraitUP also can protect plants from virus damage and induce tolerance to fungi in susceptible tomatoes.

Green Wall Israel builds walls that grow plants, flowers, vegetables, herbs, and spices, creating a green and attractive urban environment. Its vertical gardens are ideal for enhancing bare walls, built structures, and fences, and for the interior design of homes and office buildings.
The Green Wall Israel technique, which provides plants with all the vital nutrients for healthy and long-term growth, was designed and tested under a variety of conditions by a team of expert agronomists, architects, and engineers. The vertical gardens are built from modular panels that facilitate design flexibility and maintenance, turning a plain wall into a magnificent wall garden overnight.

Shacham Givat Ada Group specializes in recycling organic waste, including all types of livestock manure, green waste, farming waste, industrial food waste, organic waste from MSW, and human sludge.
Shacham also offers a wide range of products such as organic fertilizer and organo-mineral fertilizer in pellet form, bio compost, soilless growing media, and animal feed.

Univo Pharmaceuticals is a vertically integrated medical cannabis company focused on the cultivation, manufacture, distribution, and creation of products and dosage forms for medical cannabis products. The company holds initial licenses for the entire supply chain, including growing, breeding, and nursery; production of medical cannabis products; research and development; and distribution.
Univo produces its own cannabis by way of a partnership with Amit Farms, which is located in the south of Israel and designated for cannabis growth. The farm uses innovative agricultural technologies to grow high-quality cannabis and to develop Univo’s strains designed to meet specific therapeutic needs.
column11: europe, denmark, united kingdom, united states

column3:
Ashot Ashkelon supplies technologically advanced systems and components for the aerospace, defense, and automotive industries. The company specializes in manufacturing a broad range of gears and shafts for OEM jet engine producers. The shafts are constructed from a variety of materials, including steel, titanium, and nickel-based superalloys.
Ashot has the necessary facilities and equipment to develop, produce, and assemble a myriad of systems, subsystems, and components under one roof. Its manufacturing capabilities include production engineering, machining, gear cutting and finishing, deep-hole drilling and boring, heat treatments, NDT, surface finishing, and quality assurance.

Webiks developed AnSyn, a platform for overhead image analysis. AnSyn can be integrated with a variety of AI-based algorithms, helping users find images and make sense out of them. The company's solution predicts crop yield automatically, using multi-spectral satellite image data analysis combined with weather data.

Haogenplast develops and manufactures premium vinyl products used worldwide. The company's products include waterproofing membranes, decorations, and technical films. The products are used in the construction, agricultural, residential, and industrial sectors. Their applications include awnings, roofing, swimming pools, and decorative lamination for doors and windows.
column11: france, germany, israel, poland, romania, russia, spain, ukraine, united kingdom, united states

column3:
Aran Packaging designs and manufactures products for the liquid packaging industry. The company offers a wide variety of bags for bag-in-box (BIB) applications. Aran offers both aseptic and non-aseptic bags for the food industry, in sizes ranging from 2 to 1,800 liters. The company controls every step of the manufacturing process and has its own bag-making and lamination machines.
Aran's activities also include customized packaging for the high-tech, biotechnology, and biomedicine industries. One of the company's packaging solutions is used for the controlled cultivation of seaweed for biodiesel production.

Madan Technologies develops and manufactures pumping equipment, mixers, blowers, aquaculture accessories, and wastewater treatment systems. The company also distributes and markets imported products.
Madan Technologies is owned by Maagan Michael Holdings Ltd.

OptiVector develops rotors for the unmanned aerial vehicle and urban air mobility markets. Its multi-patented technology provides more flight time, flight range, and payload capacity per unit of power, with less noise than vertical-takeoff-and-landing vehicles like drones and flying cars.
OptiVector's technology also offers major fuel consumption reduction and maneuverability enhancement for marine vessels.

Appeals is developing compostable packaging solutions made from agricultural waste, with the aim of extending the shelf life of fresh produce.
Appeals will purchase raw material from growers, develop specific material, and sell the new material or specifically designed packaging to growers, wholesalers, or packaging manufacturers.

Urbanica develops, builds, and sells hydroponic products for growing vegetables, herbs, ornamental plants, and more.
The company's systems, which promote open-source, smart urban agriculture, enable users to take advantage of free space at home or work to grow their own food.

SCR engineers, designs, produces, and manufactures electronic collar tags, milk measurement devices, and multidisciplinary systems related to the dairy industry. The company’s cow-monitoring systems collect and analyze critical data points, from activity to rumination, for each individual cow, delivering heat, health, and nutrition insights to farmers.
SCR’s milking solutions include milk measurement technologies designed to simplify and streamline the milking process. The company’s herd management product offers a comprehensive system for controlling both milking and cow monitoring.

column3: Phage Biotech is a contract development company focused on tailored phage bactericides for the targeted eradication of identified bacterial strains in finite niches. The company specializes in the development of phage bactericides for use in the areas of health, food safety, veterinary medicine, agriculture, aquaculture, and fermentation.

Telman Greenhouses specializes in the production of greenhouses and turnkey projects. The company also supplies greenhouse-related equipment such as covers, curtains, irrigation systems, heating systems, and thermal screens.
The company offers several greenhouse models including the Oz, Rotem, and Lior. The Oz and Rotem lines are appropriate for growing vegetables and flowers, while the Lior model is designed for premium crops such as seaweed, sprouts, mushrooms, medicinal herbs, bio-fish, and ornamental fish.

column3:
SpecifiCare offers nutritional supplements designed to meet the specific dietary needs of individuals.
SpecifiCare evaluates and screens health experts to become part of its network. The selected experts work with the company’s pharmacists to design their own unique formulas based on what their clinical experience tells them will best address each patient’s needs.

AlgaeArt has developed a technology designed to efficiently dispose of a byproduct of reverse osmosis (RO). Water is a limiting factor in arid and semi-arid areas, and the use of RO in brackish wells presents great business potential. However, the process releases a concentrate high in salt and nitrates that requires proper disposal, which is very expensive. AlgaeArt’s technology feeds this RO concentrate to spirulina ponds.

Zigrow has developed a sensor system designed to help cannabis growers maximize yields while expending less effort and expense. The company's main unit consists of five internal sensors designed to provide a complete picture of the environment around the plant, including light, temperature, humidity, dew point, and atmospheric pressure.
The Zigrow unit is placed near the plant, and its sensors collect and store data from the air, soil, and irrigation water. This information is analyzed and displayed in a graphical, easy-to-understand interface that provides users with both current and cumulative information. The unit is also equipped with a powerful Wi-Fi module that can be accessed from any mobile device, laptop, or desktop computer.

Meteor makes netting that protects crops from insects, aviary predators, the sun, and the weather, while also ensuring growth control.
Meteor products serve a wide range of vegetable, fruit, and herb growers; are tested and proven to suit a large variety of climates and environments; and comply with the strictest international standards.

Spresh is an all-natural spray used to preserve the quality of cut fruits and vegetables by preventing browning and maintaining the natural flavor and texture for up to 24 hours. The carefully balanced solution ensures that all of the produce's nutritional value is retained when it is treated.
Egglogix is the developer of Eggxer, a device that scrambles eggs inside the shell. The company's technology is designed to encourage children to eat the entire egg, including the yolk.

Organis has developed insect repellents derived from the edible turmeric plant. The active ingredients form the basis of a diverse family of products for the agricultural, industrial, hospitality, urban, and home environments.
Organis’s products are natural, environmentally friendly, and completely healthy and safe for humans and animals in all settings, including around and on food. Classified by the U.S. FDA as Generally Recognized as Safe (GRAS), the safety profile is exceptional even among natural insect-control products.

SodaStream is a global manufacturer, distributor, and marketer of home carbonation systems. The company's system allows users to carbonate water, add flavors, and enjoy high-quality sparkling beverages at home.
The company aims to reduce polluting plastic bottles by providing consumers with an alternative way to consume beverages.

column3: Ripen is developing RFP, which is a bag that can quickly ripen avocados and other fruit. The product organically speeds up the natural ripening process. The bag indicates when the avocado is fully ripe, and it is recyclable and biodegradable.

Sciroot is an agricultural knowledge-management company that has developed a solution for irrigation management. The company's system includes a designed geotextile, sensor, pressure transducer, transmitter, and proprietary algorithm.
The Sciroot system is designed to be installed at the beginning of the season. The plant roots grow within the geotextile and are continuously monitored by the system, which transmits the status to the cloud. Root, field, and weather data are analyzed by an algorithm to provide irrigation recommendations. The farmer receives crop status data and irrigation recommendations via the associated app.

ELTA Systems develops defense systems, specializing in electromagnetic sensors (e.g. radar, electronic warfare, and communications) and integrated solutions. Its products are designed for intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance, early warning and control, self-protection and self-defense, target acquisition, and fire control applications.
The company's components and subassemblies are designed and produced in-house, enabling ELTA Systems to offer comprehensive solutions tailored to the specific requirements of its customers and users.

Canonic aims to develop and bring to market medical-grade cannabis using a genomic approach. The company will initially focus on creating improved cannabis varieties, focusing on yield, stability, and specific metabolite composition.
The company is a subsidiary of Evogene. Canonic’s development efforts will be based on the utilization of Evogene’s computational predictive biology platform, which has already demonstrated success in addressing similar objectives for other crops.

New-Create is developing autonomous robots that can hover quietly in place for long periods of time. The company's patent-protected technology allows the robots to maintain equilibrium while consuming very little energy.

HevenDrones aims to disrupt to drone industry by developing actionable drones capable of completing a wide variety of tasks while remaining user-friendly. The company has developed a patent-pending stability mechanism that enables drones to carry uneven payloads of up to 45 kilograms for over 30 minutes.
HevenDrones develops new prototypes in rapid time at its advanced laboratory and has the ability to create custom drone-based solutions for a wide range of civilian and military use cases.
MyPips is an online ordering platform for local businesses and producers.

Rafael Advanced Defense Systems designs, develops, manufactures, and supplies a wide range of high-tech defense systems for air, land, sea, and space applications, including air defense, missile, targeting, electronic warfare, guided weapons, and underwater systems.
For homeland security applications, Rafael’s Security Integrated Systems offer threat detection, identification, and deterrence along with comprehensive situational management to protect seaports, coastlines, offshore critical infrastructure, and borders.

column3:
Heliodrone is developing a regenerative power technology designed to independently recharge multi-rotor drone batteries with no human assistance or pre-setup infrastructure needed.
By enabling drones to recharge independently, the company’s technology transforms drones into fully autonomous machines while also unlocking new opportunities for long-duration and long-distance missions.

Polymer Logistics is a leading provider of one-touch, retail-ready packaging (RRP) solutions to retailers worldwide. The company provides world-class plastic container and pallet pooling services, working closely with manufacturers, suppliers, packers, and retailers alike to ensure cost-effective logistics solutions and maximum in-store product availability.
Polymer Logistics’ extensive line of returnable transport, storage, and display products includes collapsible bins; folding, nesting, and stackable crates; and reusable dollies and pallets. More environmentally friendly than traditional one-way transit packaging, these products offer substantial cost benefits and are robust enough to withstand the rigorous demands of retail supply chain logistics for many years.

FlyTech provides advanced aviation services and solutions based on unmanned aircrafts systems (UAS), including training and handling complex regulatory procedures. The company operates in the commercial and internal security sectors and provides aviation services based on the advanced UAS that it owns.
FlyTech has longstanding connections with commercial and government agencies in the fields of infrastructure, renewable energy, and law enforcement, and with organizations mapping and protecting the environment.

APG Aero Systems designs and manufactures transformational UASs for industrial, commercial, and military applications. In addition, the company provides aeronautical engineering and consulting services to aircraft developers and the military.
APG's mission is to design and deliver UAS solutions that set the standard in commercial, civil, and military flight and transform global industry milestones into routine operations.

AerialGuard Ltd develops a combination of onboard sensors and processors for high-level autonomy in unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs). The autonomy mechanics can be controlled by an operator from a ground station, and clients can benefit from intelligence metrics transmitted via the cloud.
Inspired by the human decision-making process, AerialGuard employs a UAV navigation program architecture that enables context-based mission planning, complex sense-and-avoid capabilities, following and tracking, and other intelligent navigation behavior.

Wings&Rotors Ltd develops unmanned gyrocopters for use in agriculture, homeland security, and medical evacuations.
The company’s GyroCop-11 is an advanced, affordable mini-UAV system that provides real-time day and night imagery data. The stability and controllability of the GyroCop-11 makes it suitable for challenging terrain, such as mountains and forests, where precision landing is required.

Emefcy is a wastewater treatment company developing and commercializing energy-efficient and cost-effective wastewater treatment and reuse products. The company has developed two technologies, MABR and EBR, which address limitations in municipal and industrial plants.
The Emefcy Membrane Aerated Biofilm Reactor (MABR) is a modular, decentralized wastewater treatment process that requires just 10% of the energy used by conventional technologies. This technology is based on spiral-wound respiring membranes that provide oxygen to the process and support the growth of a nitrifying biofilm. Through an integrated process of simultaneous nitrification and denitrification, the MABR produces high-quality effluent with less operational input.

Renergy develops an energy recovery system for membrane-based desalination plants, based on an isobaric pressure exchanger operating with high efficiency and reducing the capital cost of energy recovery solutions.
The system removes the need for a booster pump, utilizes common construction materials, and eliminates the need for brine mixing. Ownership and operating costs are significantly lower than traditional systems.

Peak-Dynamics is a research-driven company that addresses the complexities of operating a water utility, maintaining reliability of service and assuring water quality while minimizing energy and other operational costs. Its software system, PeakWater, and optimized stochastic search algorithm technology offer management solutions to help water utilities and operations personnel realize energy savings.
PeakWater interfaces with the SCADA system, from which it collects current and historic data to monitor and control the energy efficiency aspects of the network’s operation. A new feature introduced by the system involves a comparative analysis of energy supplier tariffs. By ensuring compliance with contractual demands and constraints, PeakWater allows water authorities to take advantage of the increasingly open private energy market.

Drying Sludge Technology (DST) is a technology startup company that is trying to resolve the economical and environmental issues that sludge drying creates. DST's patented technology improves sewage sludge quality as an agricultural fertilizer and as energy feed stock material.
The company is developing additional technologies to further improve wastewater treatment plants' operational profitability and compliance with environmental regulations.

Regulus Cyber is focused on disrupting the GNSS market with an innovative software-only, system-agnostic connected solution designed to detect, protect, and mitigate smart spoofing.
The company’s Pyramid GNSS is a big data spoofing protection software that can equip any existing GPS system with resilient, state-of-the-art PNT capabilities. Pyramid GNSS revolutionizes how a satellite’s position, velocity, and time – critical for numerous systems, including automotive, infrastructure, communication, telecom, mobility, and financials – are protected.

Eshet Eilon specializes in the design and manufacture of a complete line of equipment for the treatment and sorting of fresh fruits, vegetables, and chicks. The company’s systems manage the entire process, from receiving the product to dumping, hot water treatment, cleaning, waxing, drying, sorting, grading, and packing.
The company also offers a green sanitation system designed for medical cannabis, eggs, and extending the shelf life of fruit, as well as an automatic grading machine for large retail companies.

column3: RoboTiCan develops robotic technologies and autonomous solutions. The company provides a wide range of custom-made aerial and ground autonomous mobile platforms and ROS algorithm solutions for the defense industry, academia, private sector, and governments worldwide.

column3:
Pulvit Industries is the developer of an ultrasound-based technology for the extraction of the food additive pectin. Its technology enables pectin to be produced from orange, apple, or beet peels by creating a cavitation effect on the peel’s cell walls.
The company provides a green, zero-waste, eco-friendly technology, without the use of harmful acids or ethanols.
column11: europe, western europe, eastern europe, asia, global

column3:
GFA (Grow Fish Anywhere) Advanced System has developed and implemented a fully closed, zero-discharge aquaculture system that is suitable for both freshwater and saltwater fish. The system prevents environmental pollution and can operate in any climate regardless of the availability of water resources or proximity to the sea.
GFA uses anaerobic water treatment for nitrate removal and the digestion of organic solids. Water rich with organic particles is taken from the bottom of the fish tanks and collected in a central sedimentation basin, where solid settling and digestion, oxygen uptake, and denitrification take place.

Oplon Pure Science is a materials science company that develops protective products, coatings and processes based on a novel polymer compound.
Oplon’s coatings prevent the colonization of microbes by creating a protective physical shield on surfaces. In the case of milk, an open container with Oplon’s coating can keep milk fresh for more than 30 days, and the milk will not spoil even when stored at a warm room temperature. Preserving milk’s freshness this way — without chemical preservatives or antibiotics — profoundly alters the costs, methods, value chain, and practices of milk production, consumption, and delivery. The technology can be used for meat packaging and water bottles.

BreedIT develops agro-breeding solutions for plant breeders and researchers.
The company's iBreedIT-Intelligent Decision Support System (IDSS) was developed to optimize the breeding processes for corporations, research, and government institutions. The software generates and disseminates knowledge to help breeders plan, manage, and analyze their data and perform research activities quickly and effectively. The system is tailor-made according to a breeder's specific needs, crop, and breeding goals.

Ecofer Fertigation Technologies develops and markets advanced automated systems for dissolving and mixing soluble fertilizers.
The company’s flagship product, the Fertiwise system, allows farmers to improve crop yields with precise liquid fertilizer formula preparation, eliminating the time and costs associated with manual preparation procedures, while ensuring streamlined inventory management. The entire operation is performed on-site, giving growers unprecedented control and flexibility to easily adjust liquid fertilizer formulas throughout the growing cycle.

EdenShield has developed a family of natural, nontoxic products designed to protect crops against insect damage. Its products are based on extracts of plants indigenous to the Judean Desert.
The company’s proprietary aromatic ingredients mask plant odors, mitigating insect attraction, and the material maintains its efficacy throughout the entire growing season, as insects do not develop a resistance to it.
column11: albania, greece, israel, macedonia, mexico, portugal, spain, united kingdom, united states

column3:
Lesico CleanTech focuses on developing and commercializing sustainable water treatment technologies that recycle or significantly reduce the volume of liquid waste, primarily desalination-rejected brine. The company’s solutions are designed to help users comply with stringent regulations and save on real estate, installation, and operational costs.
Lesico CleanTech participates in collaborative research and development projects with the Department of Water Research at Ben Gurion University and receives the support of the Office of the Chief Scientist in Israel.

SolEx Water wastewater treatment enables one-stage separation from minerals and hydrocarbons, generating fresh water without extensive use of heat or energy. SolEx Water's technology is designed to handle high-contaminate process wastewater streams such as that from oil and gas production.
The SolEx Water WET process is solvent extraction-based and employs a non-toxic and widely used industrial solvent that is fully recyclable and can be made from renewable resources. The WET process is laboratory proven and uses common, off-the-shelf equipment.

SPC Tech has developed a modular smart water hub that makes water systems easy to change, maintain, or upgrade, without any modifications to the existing water system structures. The company also produces patented, smart pressure-regulating valves that significantly reduce leakages and the risk of bursts in residential water pipes, minimizing water loss, damage, and energy waste.

Advanced Brine Solutions provides a reliable and cost-effective brine treatment solution primarily for the food and beverage industry and landfill sites. 
Advanced Brine Solutions uses a confined evaporation approach, which increases the evaporation rate and ensures that there are no hazardous emissions or environmental risks. The entire evaporation process is undertaken within a confined space, making the process fully controlled and easily adjustable to the customers' needs.

ECC TECH has developed an ultra-sonic cleaning treatment technique for fruits and vegetables. The company's approach uses specialized parameters, based on acoustic power density and a variety of frequencies, suited for the particular cleaning of certain types of crops.
ECC TECH's treatment can remove fungi, viruses, and by-products of decaying pesticides that contain elements like flour, chlorine, phosphor, sulphur, and other hazardous remains.
GammaSeed is developing seed analysis solutions based on artificial intelligence and image processing to help ensure seed quality, purity, and health.

InPlant Technologies is the developer of a platform delivery technology designed to increase the mobility of active agrochemical ingredients (AI) in plants to increase their activity and reduce the required dosage, resulting in higher yields and lower environmental impact.
The company’s technology packages the AI inside nano-sized particles composed of inexpensive GRAS materials. The nanoparticles effectively penetrate the plant and transport the agrochemicals through different routes within the plant (symplast and apoplast, basipetal and acripetal flow), ultimately releasing the cargo within the plant cells.

Virentes is developing a high-throughput robot and multi-rootstock grafting technology to replace the current method of grafting, which is primarily manual and carried out one plant at a time.
Virentes’ robot grafts plants using specially designed grafting arms while automatically performing all accompanying activities, including trimming, clearing, and disinfecting. The technology is designed for ease of use and low maintenance, and will replace hundreds of laborers, reducing current grafting costs by approximately 30%.

Algalo Industries has developed an innovative process for growing algae that reduces production costs while achieving faster growth rates.
The company has successfully grown nannochloropsis sp., isochrysis sp., porphyridium sp., spirulina sp., and chlorella sp., and is now focusing on cultivating haematococcus pluvialis for its astaxanthin content. Astaxanthin pigment is the most potent antioxidant known in nature, and has been scientifically proven to be more effective than any other carotenoid.

Amaizz is an agritech company dedicated to developing products designed to minimize losses caused by spoilage and degradation throughout the handling, storage, and processing stages of agricultural commodities.

DryCan has developed a strainer that enables a clean way to drain unnecessary liquid from food cans without having to touch the jagged edges of the tin. The strainer is made of a food-grade polypropylene (not bisphenol-A), which is sterilization-resistant.

In April 2016, DryCan signed a long-term strategic partnership with Caniel, a global manufacturer of canning cans, to distribute the product and implement it as a standard in the food can industry.

Nutrisher provides a comprehensive platform for knowledge-based solutions in the areas of nutrition, health, and wellness. The company’s platform includes a multi-industry product kit designed to help companies boost sales, cut costs, win customer loyalty, and gain valuable business intelligence. The Nutrisher Analyzer is an API that analyzes recipes in real time. Its solutions are composed of antagonistic bacteria and a powder formulation of essential oils.

Its oil formulation overcomes the high phytotoxicity of essential oils and allows for effective use against bacterial diseases without harming the environment. Applications for CMM (tomatoes), black root (crucifers), ESCA (grapevines), and HLB (citrus greening) are under different stages of product development.

The material drives an increase in output water flux without affecting salt rejection, resulting in an improvement to the membrane's energy efficiency and a reduction in the cost of desalination.

Aquanity develops devices that use free-flowing energy, a technology that combines natural and environmentally sound ideas with digital technologies to revitalize water used on a daily basis.
The Aquanity water revitalization device is made of stainless steel, has no movable parts or magnets, and contains no perishable materials. Its purpose is to enhance the taste and texture of tap water and to improve the quality of drinking water.

Hazan Sprayers creates and manufactures garden, urban, and field power sprayers and spraying equipment ranging from 80 to 1,200 liters for crop protection. Hazan Sprayers also imports and represents European and American brands of pumps, engines, and accessories for crop protection machinery.
The company holds the quality management ISO 9001 rating. Its products are manufactured according to European standards and bear the CE standard.
column12: cherry, olive 100, palm 200, kiwi 300, blueberry 600, papaya 400, apricot 600, balsam 1000, carambola 1200

column3: Agrosif develops machinery for fruit harvesting. Using technology in the areas of mechanics, hydraulics, computers, and robotics, the company has developed a digital tree shaker capable of adjusting its shaking pattern to improve fruit-detachment percentages, resulting in increased yields.

Arbel offers a variety of complete turnkey project solutions and packing machines for liquids and viscid materials. Its products are designed for the food, dairy, and cosmetics industries.
The company began its operations by manufacturing equipment for the milk-processing field and has since expanded its activities to include the planning and supply of complete solutions for food-processing lines.

Flux is focused on building the world’s largest co-op for environmental data. Using a tokenized incentive layer, Flux provides growers with an opportunity to monetize their data when it is used to create tangible insights for other users on the network.
Flux has also created military-grade IoT hardware, distributed storage, and a blockchain-based AI system designed to help people all over the globe participate in sustainable practices for a future of abundance for all.

Sadot Irrigation Systems makes irrigation, fertigation, filtration, and control systems for agricultural, landscape and turf, and sports applications.
Sadot is active in all aspects of the irrigation business in Israel and abroad, including production of a large and diverse line of "Shibolet" platforms for irrigation and fertigation applications; designing, marketing, integrating, assimilating, and maintaining control systems for irrigation and fertigation applications; and managing the distribution, marketing, and after-sales service of irrigation equipment.
column12: shibolet, talgil computing & control, bermad control valves, amiad filtration systems, galcon controllers

column3: Top I Vision develops and manufactures high-performance, cost-effective tactical airborne surveillance systems. All Top I Vision solutions correspond to advanced C4ISR concepts and offer parallel data sharing with any C4I center. The company’s products are available as stand-alone turnkey products or as comprehensive, integrated multilevel surveillance systems customized to the client’s specific requirements.
column12: ground control station, casper 250 mini uav, t.a.s.

column3: SmarTap has developed a smart connected shower consisting of a patented e-valve and digital controller. The shower valve precisely measures and controls temperature, pressure, flow, and volume. It also includes end-to-end connectivity infrastructure so that all the data is passed to the company's proprietary cloud. The shower can be controlled by smartphone app, Amazon Echo, and Google Home and fully integrates into smart homes with if-this-then-that applets. SmarTap provides 24/7 monitoring of pipes, water/energy savings, and more.
column11: czech republic, france, germany, israel, italy, south africa, spain, united kingdom, united states

column3: Syrinjector is developing a digital solution for the rapid, controlled, and traceable mass-vaccination of livestock. Based on a portable automated syringe gun and software, the company’s accurate and safety-conscious solution provides digital capabilities and data management options.

Astronautics C.A. develops and supplies high-tech airborne, land, and naval defense systems worldwide. Its products are battle proven and complement its parent company’s extensive offerings to ensure battlefield superiority.
The company’s airborne solutions for fixed and rotary-wing platforms include advanced computers and displays, video/data multiplexers, engine data concentrators, electronic flight bags, digital maps, tactical mission systems, EICAS, and other avionics consoles and systems.

SimiGon is the developer of the SIMbox platform, which offers solutions for modeling, simulation, and training and can be used to create simulation content of any type for any purpose. The company's user-friendly SIMbox Toolkit is designed to enable non-programmers to rapidly create simulation content.
SimiGon's partners include government and blue chip organizations as well as small businesses.

B.L. Advanced Ground Support Systems (BL) manufactures ground support equipment for aircraft and military products for ground forces.
The company’s primary products are bomb loaders, aircraft tugs, and hydraulic power supply units. Other products include truck-mounted missile launchers, surveillance vehicles, and unmanned ground vehicles (UGVs).
column12: hpu, hts-101, att-ii, bl-1, bl-2, bl-3, mini bl-1

column3: Hi-Cap Formulations has developed a photobioreactor for cultivating a thin, highly dense layer of microalgae in flexible plastic sleeves. The horizontal sleeves float on ponds and have no superstructure. Carbon dioxide is used to inflate the air space and float the sleeves, and is also mixed into the algal medium as needed for photosynthesis by using low-energy mini near-shear wave generators. The company’s design requires no compressors or pumps for gas exchange and mixing.

Tecto manufactures and develops grading machines for the flower and rootstock industries. The company's machines are designed to save time and minimize labor costs in the post-harvest production process. The grading process's vision system makes it possible to evaluate elements of the flower, including its length, width, weight, color, and scale of opening.
Tecto also customizes machines to grower specifications.

SpaceIL is a nonprofit organization created to land the first Israeli spacecraft on the moon: the Beresheet lander.
SpaceIL began as part of the Google Lunar X Prize, which offered $30 million in prizes to inspire teams to develop low-cost methods of robotic space exploration. The SpaceIL entry planned to meet the requirement to travel 500 meters on the lunar surface by having the lander hop, using rocket engine propulsion, from its landing site to another site more than 500 meters away.

Terraflex Industries manufactures flexible hoses, tubing, and PVC compounds. The company operates its own extrusion plant and compounding facilities. The Terraflex product line includes PVC, PU, and NBR/PVC hoses, including garden, coil, agricultural and marine, fire-fighting, gas, food-grade, dairy, and medical hoses.
Terraflex also produces standard and customized PVC compounds. All Terraflex compounds are lead-free. The wide variety of available soft and rigid PVC compounds allows for the production of cables, seals, food-grade bottles, injection molding, bath mats, cable tunnels, and medical devices.
column11: global, belarus, brazil, chile, china, colombia, costa rica, cyprus, germany, greece, india, italy, mexico, netherlands, new zealand, paraguay, philippines, serbia, spain, turkey, united kingdom, united states, vietnam

column3:
Tactical Robotics focuses on the development of air vehicle configurations based on a license from Urban Aeronautics for the unmanned military and homeland security markets.
The company developed the Cormorant, a compact, unmanned, single-engine, vertical-take-off-and-landing aircraft. Internal lift rotors enable the Cormorant to fly inside obstructed (e.g. mountainous, wooded, or urban) terrain where helicopters are unable to operate. Tactical Robotics is also collaborating with ADAMA to develop the Ag-Cormorant, a solution for unmanned aerial spraying.

RCK breeds repeatable and stable hybrid cannabis seeds for both the medical and recreational markets. RCK seeks to usher in a new era of cannabis agriculture through methodological, marker-assisted cannabis breeding and the use of proprietary technologies.
The company is licensed for the entire production chain, including growing, processing, and distribution, as well as for R&D. Its facilities include an indoor growing room for R&D, a supportive laboratory, and a specially designed greenhouse for breeding and cultivation.

NovaGreen has developed a commercial technological platform that enables the disinfection of cannabis on site using cold plasma. Local staff can operate the disinfection and acquire the necessary technical capabilities with professional training.
The lab prototype for initial technology evaluation has shown 99% disinfection efficacy with no damage to the flower properties for cannabinoids, while providing fast and effective disinfection to a wide range of bacteria and fungi.
Dairyionics has developed a dairy farm management solution designed to optimize cow comfort and productivity. The company seeks to transform the dairy farming experience.

Eco-Net (the Ecology Network) develops smart, connected, digital fishing lures tailored to the Leisure and Sports Fishing markets. This IoT lure, the Eco-Popper, supplies fishermen with detailed metrics to enhance their experience.
Eco-Popper sends a real-time, wireless, underwater HD-video stream to smartphone or tablet, from which local and cloud analysis is performed, providing the angler with relevant metrics in real time. The lure is equipped with a series of sensors that transmit water data metrics to a central cloud application and database in order to monitor water quality whenever and wherever it is used.

Rolla RWT develops foldable hotplates. The company's HotMat is made with mica heating elements to produce concentrated, even heating throughout the surface, no matter the dish size.
The HotMat requires a third of the storage space of standard warming trays. In addition, the HotMat is lightweight and user friendly.

LipoGreen provides soil rehabilitation services using a technology that enables environmental conservation. The company's technology treats polluted soil without having to move it to an external site.
The company has developed two soil treatments based on its technology. The first is the physical treatment, and its goal is to physically wash pollutants (oils) from the ground. LipoGreen's washing solution causes the hydrocarbon compounds in the soil to turn into liquid. After rinsing, the mixture, which includes the organic substances emitted from the soil, is taken for gravitational separation by "decanting" (separation of fat from the liquid mixture). The second treatment is biological and accelerates the decomposition of hydrocarbons in the soil.

Terrascan Labs Ltd uses drones for aerial mapping services, 3D modeling, photography, and remote sensing. The company develops unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and on-board technology designed to capture oblique and stereoscopic photographs.
Information collected by Terrascan's UAVs undergoes object and anomaly detection, volume measurement, and other types of analysis. Vertical and oblique photography is achieved with mounted HD digital cameras. The system can be implemented anywhere in the world, with processing performed via the cloud in Israel.

Targene, in collaboration with PlantArcBio, develops manufacturing capabilities for active plant ingredients. Targene produces cannabis extracts in a controlled environment, using tissue culture technologies to grow cannabis cells commercially in sterile lab conditions, yielding accurate and consistent compound dosages for the pharmaceutical industry.
Targene also performs advanced strain optimization using gene editing and other advanced molecular techniques, producing personalized strains for end users and the pharmaceutical industry.

Cecilia.ai is an interactive bartender that can be customized for any event or business.
Powered by conversational AI and voice recognition abilities, Cecilia makes delicious cocktails crafted by acclaimed mixologists, chats with customers, tells jokes, promotes users' brands, and provides an unforgettable experience to new and returning visitors.

Nando is a drone-based autonomous platform that offers a wide variety of solutions. Drones can perform surveillance and patrols autonomously without any human intervention. The products are mission-specific and depend on the needs of the client.
Nando's drones can hover above a site for up to 70 minutes at a time and are capable of detecting movement and the human form at a range of up to 250 meters. The combination of the drones' superior field of vision and exceptional flight time means that a single eye in the sky is capable of replacing perimeter patrol at a fraction of the cost.

NeuroPet is developing a brain–machine interface activity system for animals that enables humans to know their thoughts and feelings in real time.
The system uses proprietary, real-time algorithms, deep artificial intelligence, and machine learning, which run on the cloud and can be read via any web interface, mobile device, or voice text.
The brain activity monitor relies on a single EEG channel and produces unique brain activity biomarkers. This is enabled by advanced mathematical signal processing and sensitive electronics. The main effort is currently focused on verticals such as pet owners and health and remote care. It may also be suitable for support in medical research, such as for drug development, monitoring effects over time.

Plantae aims to develop solutions for the global food and beverage industry and products to transform global nutrition and environmental security.
The company is focused on developing plants enriched with health-related compounds for key human health challenges, advanced genome editing, and protein optimization technologies combined with plant tissue culture and disruptive agricultural approaches. The improved plants will take on a vital role in both the cellular agriculture and vertical farming revolutions.

ParagonH2 manufactures a device designed to supply electricity and clean water simultaneously while being driven by hydrogen instead of electricity. The company's device addresses the growing water crisis, enabling users to purify water without damaging the environment.

ANINA creates ready-to-consume meal capsules that are 100% natural, rich in vegetables and nutrients, easy to use, designed by designers, and made from fresh ugly produce. The company's capsules aim to offer consumers taste, health, convenience, sustainability, and excitement.
This company is a known business entity but lacks sufficient data to support a standard Finder profile.

Lingord provides crop protection solutions for farmers all over the world. With more than 20 years of experience in over 30 countries worldwide, Lingord understands each grower’s specific needs and can offer the most suitable solutions for their crops.

RobotPicks is developing a state-of-the-art autonomous harvester designed to ensure optimal picking of high quality crops, starting with cannabis flowers and aiming to expand to general crops in the future. Using an advanced image analysis and learning system, the robot will detect and pick the flowers, clean away the leaves, and gently place the flowers in a container.
The company’s innovative system will be mounted on an autonomous vehicle that will move across the greenhouse to harvest the flowers automatically, efficiently, and accurately. The robotic system will add value and economic growth to the grower, reducing harvest costs and improving picking quality and accuracy compared to the manual picking practices currently in use.

Moonscape is a lunar services and payload transportation company that provides necessary services like communication relay and imaging while delivering payloads to the Moon.
Moonscape's vision is to support humankind's effort of reaching the Moon sustainably and responsibly, as humanity's first step towards the rest of the solar system and beyond. The company intends to deploy orbiters in lunar orbit to provide imaging and communications. Those orbiters will also have payload bays, which will be used for in-orbit payloads and small landers.

Agwa is a hydroponic vegetables-as-a-service (VaaS) platform that uses AI technology to help people grow their own vegetables.
The company’s vision is to enable people to eat ultra-fresh, healthy, nutrient-rich vegetables straight from farm to table while eliminating pesticide use, transportation pollution, and plastic packaging.

Agmatix is an agriculture informatics company that develops data-driven solutions for the agriculture industry. The company's data-driven solutions standardize agronomic data, provide actionable insights for agricultural professionals and growers, improve crop yield, and promote sustainable agriculture.
Agmatix is part of ICL Group Ltd.

Aroma-Tix specializes in international cloud-based IoT-sensor machine-learning solutions. The company's mission is to help medical cannabis growers all over the world predict the appearance of harmful pathogens on their plants.
Grow-V is developing an AI algorithm allowing growers, farmers, and breeders to save time, labor costs, and money.

First Airborne is the developer of Windborne, a proprietary drone onboard sensor for wind-turbine performance inspection tasks including power curve validation, nacelle misalignment degree, and additional performance insights. The platform can operate in real time and under schedule in any weather conditions including in marine missions.

Fermata develops sustainable computer vision solutions for precise plant monitoring in greenhouses.
The company's solutions enable the use of imagery data to automate the visual monitoring process, including early disease identification, pest detection, and plant growth control.
Use of Fermata technology can significantly reduce crop losses and pesticide and chemical usage.
Pitriya provides the highest-quality organic superfoods on the market with main focus on the therapeutic value medicinal mushrooms offer.

Wonder Robotics is the developer of WonderLand, a solution that enables vertical take-off and landing (VTOL) drones to land safely and completely autonomously on any uncharted, unprepared, and unattended site without operator involvement or supervision of any kind.
WonderLand is a self-contained airborne POD with complete onboard autonomy and does not depend on any external communication or GPS reception. It meets broad situational awareness requirements for navigation, obstacle detection and avoidance, and safe emergency landings, with applications ranging from package delivery to infrastructure inspection, mapping, and more.

BugEra develops and produces novel black soldier fly (BSF) strains and specializes in genetic engineering for insects for future food security.
BugEra increases the fly's natural traits by introducing genetic editing and modifications, resulting in the patent-pending Modified Black Soldier Fly (M-BSF) Platform.
The M-BSF Platform gives rise to novel, sustainable, and safe products, creating new potential markets and revenue streams for the BSF industry.

AgriFriend aims to help smallholder farmers increase their yield productivity by making agricultural knowledge and expertise accessible to everyone, everywhere. AgriFriend automatically creates a customized step-by-step learning process, from planting to harvest, according to the user's particular needs and conditions.
AgriFriend uses different visual tools and techniques to make the learning process the most effective and practical.

Blix is the developer of kwiX, an intelligent blending platform with pre-portioned smart cups that can blend a fresh smoothie, soup, or spread in a matter of seconds with no planning or prepping and with zero cleaning. The company uses only natural ingredients – flash-frozen at their peak for optimal nutrition – for easy, instant, and wholesome blended sips and snacks, all made to order.
Blix sources the freshest ingredients possible and freezes them at peak harvest using individual quick freezing (IQF) technology. It then creates chef-curated recipes and places them into a space-saving pouch. Using smart sensors, the kwiX machine recognizes and perfectly blends each Blix recipe, and within two minutes a delicious smoothie, breakfast bowl, or spread is ready, with nothing to clean.

Eyeviation develops pilot assessment software that provides objective and reliable evaluation of pilots' cognitive performance, based on eye-tracking technology and powerful AI algorithms.
The company's first product selects the best fighter pilots for the Israeli Air Force and predicts their real in-flight performance by tracking their eyes during a test on the ground.

Atlas LTA offers a wide variety of customized lighter-than-air solutions for surveillance, communications, entertainment, tourism, and cargo transportation.
Atlas's flagship project is a new family of large-capacity transport airships that will be capable of carrying oversized and overweight cargo of up to 165 tons, using safe helium buoyancy and dynamic lift made possible by low-emission hybrid-electric propulsion. Since it does not require any special infrastructure, it can land in a desert, on water, or even Arctic ice, making many hard-to-reach destinations much more accessible.

AgroCulture has developed a novel method for the fast production of avocado seedlings, in 8 months instead of 18. The method involves cloning the vegetative propagation in tissue cultures in part of the avocado plant and ensuring disease-free plants.

Agri-Light Energy Systems has developed a solar tracking system based on a proprietary agri-voltaic algorithm that enables dual usage of land, by managing the level of radiation to optimize the generation of electricity, crop cultivation, and crop yield.
The Agri-Light control model allows for dynamic control of the shading level by changing the volumetric space and placement of the solar panels. Depending on the physiological needs of the crops, the system will automatically change the position of the solar panels, creating the appropriate conditions for maximum yield and crop protection.

CannaRe converts high-volume agricultural waste into chemicals for the food and flavor, cosmetics, and pharmaceutical industries. CannaRe developed a mobile thermo-chemical technology with low energy usage and no by-products, designated for on-site treatment in the greenhouse.
Its economic foundation is based on the resulting chemical feedstock, which holds antioxidant and antimicrobial attributes.
This company is a known business entity but lacks sufficient data to support a standard Finder profile.

Wonders of Nature develops delicious, sustainable meat alternatives packed with authentic flavors, aromas, and textures. The company’s plant-based meats are designed to make it easier than ever for people to reduce or even eliminate their consumption of conventional meat.
Wonders of Nature’s plant-based meat products are climate-friendly, requiring up to 90% lower greenhouse gas emissions than the production of conventional meat. The company’s plant-based meat products are currently marketed in the form of burgers, sausages, ground meat, and kebabs, with more products forthcoming.
column12: wonders burger, wonders chorizo, wonders kebab, wonders ground

column3:
BetterSeeds is committed to providing better crops for feeding the world by use of genome-editing technology (CRISPR-Cas9).
BetterSeeds' genetic trait platform and technology contribute to agricultural sustainability by designing novel varieties that enable farmers to meet output goals while using significantly less arable land.
For this purpose, BetterSeeds has built a large plant-editing facility in Israel and holds all the necessary CRISPR licenses and proprietary technology to deliver its vision.

VitActive develops natural substitutes for chemical preservatives in food. The company's solutions are aimed at ensuring food safety and enhancement of the food brand. VitActive utilizes noncommercial super-fruit extracts to control pathogen microbes that cause diseases in food.

DOTS developed a patented sensor and system for in-situ real-time measurement of nitrate levels, enabling the optimization of fertilizer application during agricultural activity.
Following a series of laboratory and field trials, the company's proven and patented technology has shown the ability to decrease the use of agricultural resources, without lowering yields, while dramatically reducing groundwater pollution.

Ansā is the developer of a patent-pending roasting technology that heats coffee beans from the inside out. The roasting process is governed by neural networks that replace the human operator with a fully autonomous process, producing a homogenous and consistent roast every time.
The company's invention facilitates a perfect roast with environmental benefits, as it produces zero particulate matter or carbon dioxide and is up to 50 times more energy efficient than conventional roasting methods.

Bee-io Honey produces honey without bees in a process that combines natural nectar flowers with unique biological processes that turn the nectar into honey.
The company aims to develop cultured honey via an artificial bee stomach that naturally mimics the enzymatic activity and specific conditions and processes that occur in the bee's stomach. In addition, Bee-io is working on technologies to produce natural nectar to increase the capacity of honey production quickly and more efficiently.
VisiCann is developing cloud-connected, data-centric, and AI-driven technology solutions for post-harvest cannabis processing, curing, delivery, storage, and handling.

Priceless Water is developing a proprietary patented device that controls the water system electronically, enables the immediate flow of hot water; thereby saving considerable amounts of otherwise wasted water.
Torr develops solutions for the multi-ingredient snacking industry by composing food ingredients together, without using sugar to bind them.

Peas Of Bean is a clean label and vegan food brand producing a variety of veggie balls and burgers made from fresh ingredients and free of allergens, sugar, and preservatives. The burgers are baked and filled with fresh vegetables and herbs.
Peas Of Bean is currently developing allergen and sugar-free vegan patties.

Seanergy Electric develops solutions related to different aspects of clean technology and sustainability, particularly in the fields of energy and water. The company also consults with governments and municipalities worldwide.
Seanergy Electric is currently focused on developing the HydroTop, a new type of water pump designed to work on mechanical principles only. The HydroTop pump consists of an upstream water route with "reverse gravity" chambers and tanks driven upwards, with a valve system that is designed to create an efficient mechanism.

Solano Pet Care is focused on developing and manufacturing parasite pesticide solutions for pets. Solano has developed a technology for the slow release of pesticides from a plastic material from which waterproof pest control collars for dogs can be manufactured.
The company's pest control collar, Soltick, comes with a slow-release mechanism. In addition to the pesticide, the collar releases perfumed aromatic oils that neutralize bad odors.
column12: ecolife, soltick, soltif, solpreme, relax-sol, solflex, endosol, protecsol

column3: ViewNetic is an AgTech start-up developing an autonomous, high-resolution pest and disease detection system. Its AI-enhanced system will be the cornerstone of an autonomous, end-to-end detection, analysis, and treatment platform for the global greenhouse market.

FlightOps has developed a drone-agnostic control system designed to help drone service providers scale their operations by enabling the management of a variety of drones within one operating environment. The company's system operates directly from the cloud to allow coordinated swarms of drones to share the skies safely, simply, and beyond visual line of sight.
FlightOps overcomes traditional range limits by using LTE, 4G/5G, and SATCOM backup to allow users to operate their fleet for long distances from anywhere in the world.

SoLED is an LED-based off-grid water disinfection device designed for infrastructure-limited areas such as developing countries and deserts. The patented device provides low-cost disinfection with minimal human intervention required for installment and operation.

invicTOO developed a rule-writing language for any control system, with all the benefits of software in an English-like syntax, with an automatically created dashboard. invicTOO's language, TOO, is suitable for cloud or on-premises infrastructure, and no prior programming knowledge is needed to write the rules.
TOO is as powerful and expressive as any computer language but is reduced to rule-based logic and requires no special skills.
column11: northern europe, israel, netherlands, united states

column3: Diptera.ai develops an affordable subscription service to receive sterile male insects that suppress the wild pest population upon release. This is made possible through a scientific breakthrough that allows sex-sorting insects at the larval stage using artificial intelligence.

Robotic Perception is developing autonomous vehicles for farming that provide precision spray solutions, mechanical treatment for weeds, and continuous monitoring of crops and plants using high-resolution imagery and a web-based crop management interface.
The robotic platform integrates high-resolution imagery, inertial sensors, and 3D sensors with actuators that include a spray module and mechanical treatment for weeds. Proprietary software supports accurate operation even in GPS-denied areas for extended periods of time, and uses AI and deep-learning modules for crop and plant condition analysis and improved yields.

Grace Breeding is an Israeli agricultural biotechnology company developing proprietary on-farm technologies that replace synthetic fertilizers, improve crop yield, and promote sustainable environmental practices.
The company's proprietary non-disruptive, environmentally sustainable fertilizer, offered through its subsidiary Nitrogen Fixation Technologies Ltd, reduces air, soil, and groundwater contamination and enhances nitrogen uptake by crops.
column11: north america, south america, europe, southern africa, oceania, israel

column3: PhytoPharma developed CannaBeeZ, cannabis-derived honey that delivers the benefits of cannabis, like pain relief, sleep support, and stress and anxiety alleviation, without intoxicating effects or chemical interference. It contains a measurable concentration of active cannabinoids of less than 0.3%.

Neopterix Solutions is developing zero-residue, environmentally friendly solutions for the control of fruit flies.
Neopterix Solutions operates within the framework of the Trendlines Agtech business incubator.

Ripe-Guard is developing a technology platform for predicting the shelf life of fruit and vegetables. The company’s goal is to reduce the massive depreciation and waste that typify the $2.3 trillion fruit and vegetable industry and result in the disposal of up to 45% of all produce grown.
Ripe-Guard’s shelf-life prediction system will make it simple and affordable to obtain accurate predictions of the dates at which produce will ripen and spoil. This will in turn result in new efficiencies across the value chain to save money and manpower, expand available food supplies, and enhance the sustainability of the global fruit and vegetable industries.

Entoprotech is a circular economy company engaged in organic/food waste treatment and processing. The company harnesses the unique qualities of insects, particularly black soldier flies (Hermetia illucens), in order to convert food waste into variety of advanced products.
Among Entoprotech's products are defatted insect meal (high-protein replacement for fishmeal); high-quality insect fat, which is currently used as feed and has many potential uses in cosmetics and pharmaceuticals; and frass (leftovers from larvae metabolic activity), which is a high-quality fertilizer.

PCM Space takes a multidisciplinary approach to precise habitat modeling and execution, with the goal of creating protective, sustainable, efficient, and environmentally friendly habitats on the moon and Mars.
PCM Space integrates sustainable, eco-friendly building elements with IoT architecture, biophilic design, virtual reality, and discourse analysis technologies. Short for “protection, comfortability, and mindset,” PCM is focused on providing future Lunar and Martian settlers with some of their most basic needs.

Strix Drones is developing a fully autonomous docking system that supports multipurpose drones from any manufacturer (e.g. DJI, Yuneek, Walkera, Flying-Production, and others). The company’s fully autonomous system supports takeoff, flight, data analytics, landing, and charging, and can operate both day and night and in rough weather conditions.
Strix Drone’s capsule is deployed in the field, where it functions much like a gas station for cars. Any drone that is on a mission and low on energy can land in the Stix Drones box, recharge itself in seven minutes, and resume its mission.
