Water Flow Tech has developed a low-flow water controller that fits most water meters on the market. The controller allows existing water meters to measure low flows with maximum efficiency and thus detect small water leaks that cause significant water waste. The next series of controllers will detect leaks in real time, send alerts, and report the location of leaks in smart buildings.

Forsea is a cultivated seafood company that has licensed a platform to nourish the world with high-quality seafood while securing ocean health and wealth.
Forsea was cofounded with the Kitchen Hub Incubator.

Optium is focused on revolutionizing cellular agriculture production by using artificial intelligence to support a smooth transition to industrial-scale production, thereby ensuring that every batch of cellular (cultivated) or acellular (fermented) food product makes its way to the dinner table.
The company’s platform collects mass amounts of data from the production process and uses multiple AI engines to analyze the performance of bioreactors in real time, alerting when performance is suboptimal. By providing process analysis and uncovering otherwise neglected data, Optium allows process engineers to identify the root cause of suboptimal batches and make the necessary changes during the process in order to ensure an optimal outcome.

NoWaste is a platform that solves the problem of agricultural waste, mainly plastics and plant material residues. With NoWaste farmers can deliver their waste for recycling quickly & simply, on-demand, before this valuable material becomes unusable. Sharing valuable data with all stakeholders is our key to a cost-effective “closes the loop” process.
NoWaste facilitates the use of plastic in agriculture while preventing agricultural plastic waste at the same time.

Atifit specializes in plastics. It manufactures and distributes products made of polyethylene, polypropylene, and PVC for diverse applications in agriculture, industry, tourism, and home use.
The company's products include bags that extend the shelf-life of agricultural produce, environmentally friendly biodegradable compost bags, and packaging and protection solutions for industrial applications.

ProFuse Technology is developing a solution that aims to achieve parity between the price of cultured meat and that of animal origin. The company's efficient solution is designed to reduce production time, increase yield, and enhance the production capacity of cultured meat by accelerating the growth of muscle fiber.
ProFuse Technology's solutions and additives are based on its patent-pending technology, which activates a biochemical signaling pathway that acts at two distinct phases of myogenesis by accelerating differentiation and enhancing the fusion of myoblasts.

Novid-20 is the developer of an industrial process for extracting a particular polyphenol extract (PE) of cinnamon for the production of PE-enriched lozenges. The company's tasty, sugar-free lozenges are designed to serve as a further protection layer against viral infection, in addition to the use of masks and other safety measures, and could be used in travel kits.
Novid-20 has also developed an anti-herpes gel.

Wanda Fish is a food technology company producing a wide variety of delicious, sustainable, cell-cultured fish meat.
Wanda Fish aims to let the world eat the fish it craves while giving the marine ecosystem time to rehabilitate.

Bing Klima offers an urban agri-voltaic system that can be installed on rooftops, providing soilless agriculture-based food production and solar electricity generation. By using Bing Klima's system, customers can enjoy clean energy and natural lighting, reduce urban heat load and greenhouse gas emissions, and provide fresh produce, all while increasing their revenue.
Bing Klima sells to end customers through solar companies and partners with property owners who directly benefit from generating electricity and growing their own produce.

Fungit Biosolutions' biocontrol agent offers protection against severe fungal diseases and provides higher yield with improved nutritional value. The products will be easy to apply, safe, and effective at the pre- and post-harvest stages. The products will be scalable with seamless integration in common irrigation systems.

Treetoscope is the developer of a revolutionary IoT technology solution for measuring crop water consumption and irrigation needs in real time. The company’s technology is affordable, scalable, and easy to deploy and provides high-value actionable insights.
In addition to saving water, Treetoscope’s technology is designed to increase yield, improve fruit quality, and provide better control of harvesting windows, resulting in increased performance and profit for farmers.
column11: americas, north america, central america, south america, europe, western europe, southern europe, asia, africa, global, india, israel, italy, spain

column3: Culception is a precision agricultural technology company developing sustainable cultivation solutions. The company develops autonomous greenhouse operating systems used by cultivation networks worldwide to produce high-value crops consistently, sustainably, and at scale.

Hydrofeed developed a waterborne feeding system for any aquaculture. The solution is simple, cost effective, and can dramatically improve farms' sustainability footprint.
Hydrofeed focuses on intensive farms under upgrade. The company's solution aims to enable an 80% reduction of black diesel generator power, elevate animal welfare, reduce food waste, and stop microplastic discharged into the environment.

Imagene Foods is developing a novel-patent-protected approach that enables a cost effective platform for production of high-functional protein complex for the sustainable animal-free food industry.
By using advanced genetically modified plants , the company will create a scalable and cost-effective platform for production of REAL sustainable food without the need of farm animals.

Textree is developing a soilless culture composed of processed and manipulated textile waste. The substrate, which can be used for multiple growing cycles, addresses both the ongoing problem of textile waste and the increasing demand for soilless culture solutions.
Mush Foods grows edible mushroom mycelium to create sustainable, animal-free protein for use in the food and beverage industry.

ERGONOMIX Water Technologies has developed a patented, next-generation modular cartridge technology that enables tap companies to provide customers with ergonomic, safe, water-saving solutions that optimize form and function for an exceptional user experience.
The company’s technology allows taps to be as narrow as 18 millimeters, reducing production costs and carbon footprint while allowing for the creation of elegant new designs. The operating handles can be as small as 20 millimeters and can be located in novel places such as at the tip of the spout, close to the user. The use of these innovative ergonomic designs enables taps to be extremely easy and accurate to use, even by a small child.
column11: north america, europe, east asia, southeast asia, south asia, canada, china, india, japan
column12: black swan, parakeet, magic, mono, daisy, cubix

column3:
CarobWay aims to bring maximum value to carob-based ingredients by advancing sustainable carob cultivation, harvesting, and extraction processes. The company combines Israeli agricultural technology with European food technology solutions to derive the full goodness of the entire fruit's components (seeds and fruits). It works to bridge the gap between current supplies of carob and its demand.
CarobWay is committed to delivering all the nutritional and sustainability benefits of carob to consumers and food companies worldwide. With plans in place to establish its own production facilities, the company intends to license its production technologies to carob growers and kibblers globally and share its expertise in this field to help formulators produce innovative carob-centered products.

Yoran Imaging develops Packaging Analytical Monitoring (PAM), a non-intrusive in-line inspection system for heat-sealed packages that does not result in production slowdown. PAM combines thermal imaging technology with advanced real-time algorithms.
The solution can be used for containers, blisters, canisters, pouches, sachets, and tubes.

BlueTree is focused on developing a sugar-reduction platform for use in the beverage industry. The company aims to selectively remove sugars from natural drinks without introducing additives and while maintaining the drink’s original composition except for the sugar. BlueTree’s process is designed to be an economically viable solution for large-scale production methods.

SPV Technologies is developing smart plant valve technology based on the discovery of the mechanism that controls stomata opening, which proves that sugars close stomata via the sugar sensor hexokinase (HXK) in guard cells. Increasing the amount of HXK in guard cells allows plants to have much more efficient stomata, saving water, enhancing growth, and increasing yield.

ThermoSiv develops heating fabric weaved with carbon-based conductive yarns. ThermoSiv's technology offers safe and healthy far-infrared therapy heating, fast and uniform heat, energy efficiency, and flexible and easy integration. It is suitable for vehicles, agriculture, medicine, military and outdoor, food delivery, disinfection and pesticides, consumer goods, and construction and industrial uses.

BudUP has developed a nontoxic and non-phytotoxic solution to induce bud dormancy break. Numerous field trials on table grapes, apple, peach, and kiwi have proven that BudUp has a similar effectiveness as hydrogen cyanimide at breaking bud dormancy. BudUp is not phytotoxic even if applied on non-dormant buds.
BudUP is a fully owned subsidiary of COPIA Agro and Food Technologies Fund.

PostBoost is a crop-improvement company whose product PB provides a multifunctional biological solution for crop protection, disease resistance, pest resistance, and fruit-quality enhancement. The solution was developed by a multidisciplinary team of scientists from Israel’s Agricultural Research Organization (Volcani Center).
PB can be applied to a variety of crops and offers a wide range of solutions, with efficacy comparable to that of standard chemical products. PB can be used as a crop protection product when applied to plants, protecting them against diseases and insects, and can also be used as a fruit-quality enhancer when applied at the flowering stage or directly to fruit before harvest.

Agricam has developed a cloud-based precision agriculture solution that provides farmers, agronomists, and agricultural businesses and institutions with analytical decision-support tools for monitoring, understanding, and optimizing field yield and crop performance. The company’s platform is aided by satellite data and provides algorithm-based strategic analytical tools such as multiple growth layer maps, indices maps, graphs, and more.

ChkEat analyzes users' food to determine if they should eat it or not. It presents a health grade of food products quickly and easily by analyzing the ingredient list using a smart algorithm. Regular use of the app can help users eat healthier and safer food.

AquaSafe app enable to reduce the chance of water leakage.
The app shows statistics and graphs illustrating the usage of water.

COEXIST has created a method of collecting and analyzing data based on the feed consumed by individual cows. The company’s solution helps dairy farmers and feed suppliers by combining constant milk output with reduced feed costs and efficient decision-making about the net income of the individual cow.
COEXIST’s solution increases the cows’ health and welfare while contributing to a healthier environment by strengthening sustainability and reducing greenhouse gas and wet manure caused by overfeeding.
column12: true trough, smart gates, data driven nutrition

column3: Must-Quito develops a mechanically and automatically controlled mosquito trap that operates without power or harmful chemicals. The trap can be deployed in remote rural areas as well as in crowded cities. Must-Quito aims to reduce the risk of infection from mosquito-borne diseases.

CreamCol is a food technology company with a novel, patented technology that changes alcoholic drinks into a creamy to semi-solid texture with a high-percent alcohol content (up to 25% vol) that remains stable and has a long shelf-life.
The company works closely with alcohol and food companies to create new solutions with unique and delicious tasting experiences.

Yofix Probiotics develops and manufactures white-label vegan and soy-free fermented plant-based prebiotic and probiotic foods, based on a blend of cereals, nuts, and seeds. The first released products are plant-based yogurt alternatives and yogurt-alternative drinks, to be followed by desserts, frozen yogurts, and an ice cream base.
column11: europe, global, canada, israel, russia, switzerland, united kingdom, united states

column3:
Orgil Greenhouses is recognized as one of the worlds leading manufacturers and developers of complete greenhouse projects.
Orgil has expertize in manufacturing and installation of Greenhouse projects around the world.
Israel is a small country with limited agriculturally-productive land, limited water resources; yet Israel is universally admired as an agriculturally productive country and a net exporter of agricultural crops. This has been achieved through the innovative development of greenhouses for the production of high-end horticulture and floriculture crops for both domestic consumption and export to European markets.

Agam Advanced Agronomy has developed fertilizer, pesticide, and irrigation optimization software, which it uses to offer end-to-end solutions in the area of precision farming.
Based on input from geographical information systems (GIS), GPS, remote sensing (aerial and satellite photography), and agricultural control systems, Agam's software enables farmers to optimize location, dosage, and timing of inputs.

BioBetter has developed a cost-effective, plant-based protein expression platform to produce complex growth factors for use in cultivated meat. Its technology overcomes the limitations of traditional methods and places the cost of growth factor production at under $1 per gram.
By using tobacco plants grown in open fields as self-sustained, renewable energy-driven “bioreactors” in concert with a novel purification method, the company’s technology enables production of complex proteins at an unprecedented scale.
CelluFlux is a chemical technology startup that develops chemical processes for the production of materials and chemicals from renewable resources.
PrintDrone is a robotic flying drone, able to print murals, decorations, and advertisements on walls of public spaces, municipal structures, and buildings.

HyFeed is an automatic animal feeder powered by tap water. Using HyFeed, feeding times and quantities can be controlled and automated, as it delivers a constant supply of fresh water and a controlled amount of food. HyFeed operates on water and solar power, and requires the use of a battery only as a backup. Optional sensors and cameras can monitor the animals' feeding regimen and enable remote contact with the owner.

Prevera's mission is to eliminate microbial contamination by utilizing sustainable solutions that are effective and safe for consumers and the environment.
Based on antimicrobial peptides, Prevera developed a novel, patented disinfection solution that is effective, safe, and simple to incorporate into water purification systems, food and beverage production processes, and packaging applications.

ALTA provides agricultural solutions for farmers using unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) technology.
ALTA has designed UAVs with high-resolution agricultural surveillance technology, using patented algorithms for advanced mapping and photography, and has equipped larger UAVs with custom chemical dispersal devices. In combination, these systems provide solutions for pesticide application, optimizing time, improving accuracy, and saving labor costs.

Cannytix specializes in delivering and promoting new standards and processes for the cannabis ecosystem. The company is focused on transforming cannabis data into a significant business edge through the use of analytical models and AI technology. Cannytix has developed a cloud-based platform that collects and uses information from computerized systems and sensors placed on plants along with data from sales and consumer behavior.

AgriDat is creating a BI intelligence software for the agriculture predictive marketplace. Based on the data collected, the system will alert the user against dangers, anomalies (or any other calculation/custom alert needed), and it will identify and help users be more accurate with any decision making or action needed.
Agridat will provide farmers and any end user valuable intel about their field and surrounding.

Tadiran offers a wide range of air conditioning systems supported by its air cleaning and disinfection technologies. The company has developed cooling and heating technologies, patented air cleaning and purification features, and invested in its systems’ designs in order to create healthy breathing environments and improve indoor air quality solutions across a range of residential and commercial applications.

Sea Dream Fisheries develops and integrates land-based indoor fisheries. The company initiates the development of land-based fisheries in a variety of locations around the world in close cooperation with globally recognized aquaculture experts, technology companies, and infrastructure contractors.
Sea Dream uses Fishways technology, a new concept in the in-land aquaculture market. Fishways' patented technology uses a small, easy-to-operate bio-filtration system that operates using continued application of disposable bio-filtration capsules.

AQUALITAS Technologies strives to enable water system operators and users to make informed operational decisions based on reliable data.
Through a deep understanding of water chemistry and sensory principles, the AQUALITAS team has developed advanced machine learning and artificial intelligence models that monitor the operational stability of sensors on its proprietary water quality monitoring platform and perform automatic calibration without human interaction or cleaning.

Pots Farms aims to transform cities into clean green spaces using IoT and AI technologies. The company is developing an autonomous plant-watering device for home plant growers. The environmentally friendly product is consciously sourced and created from fully upcycled plastic bottles.
Pots Farms is also developing a fully automated, AI-based system of modular hydroponic IoT micro-farms for cities in order to establish a global marketplace for produce. Each plant’s individual habitat represents a node in the network, and by equipping these nodes with sensors and communication capabilities, Pots Farms will receive real-time information on the status and health of the node. This information is then sent to a central AI algorithm that adjusts all the inputs to the node, ensuring optimal care with minimal maintenance by the user.

Spear is a defense and homeland security company that offers a broad range of unmanned aerial solutions based on encapsulated drones. Suitable for launch from air, sea, and land, these strategic, tactical, and micro-tactical solutions create new dimensions for managing the modern battlefield.
Spear solutions are used by military, government, and civilian organizations around the globe. The company is the single-source supplier for several projects with the Israeli Ministry of Defense.

Venda Robotics specializes in robotic technology for the food industry, with a focus on the FFP cycle. The company is currently developing a robotic platform for preparing and delivering natural food.

Nutritional Growth Solutions (NGS) is building a nutrition brand for children and developing a full range of products in order to optimize children's growth and improve their physical sports performance.
NGS's product Healthy Height is a nutritional formula that was developed by physicians and nutrition experts to support and enhance children's diet to promote height. The formula, based on food components that are important for proper growth, has been shown in a clinical study to boost kids' (3–9 years old) height and weight, without a change in body-mass-index percentiles.
column11: europe, asia, middle africa, australia, canada, china, india, israel, united states

column3: Stay is a fresh food subscription service for dogs. Using ongoing biofeedback, data science, and a personal relationship with dog parents, Stay aims to help humans make conscious decisions when it comes to their dog’s nutrition.

Moonication's device is a smart cattle-tracking ear device that helps producers become more productive and profitable. Moonication transforms data into truly actionable insights about the food supply chain.

Accutures develops technology capable of 3D imaging, material classification, object recognition based on shape and material, daylight imaging (even under camouflage), and accurate temperature mapping, all in one portable device.
The company’s technology is designed for use in medical devices, industrial inspections, security applications, autonomous vehicles, agricultural monitoring, and space exploration.

BioShade is focused on solving the problem of urban heat islands using a smart, modular hydroponic system for growing shade plants. BioShade’s biological shading technology provides shading, cooling, and improved air quality.
The company’s system uses proprietary vertical hydroponics that can increase growth rate and save water compared to growing plants in soil. As a result, the system can provide significant areas of shade in a matter of months.

Hyper is developing a fully autonomous self-contained robotic store–factory hybrid capable of providing fresh, flavorful, healthy, and safe fast food that meets the demands of both the industry and the consumer.

EcoS develops genetically engineered proteins that exhibit specific toxicity to the fruit fly but are environmentally and animal-friendly. EcoS formulation in microparticles and/or nanoparticles contains, among other things, a small and non-toxic protein derived from an environmentally friendly bacterium. The formulation will be given by spray or emulsion in the ground near the trees and will be designed to attract and eliminate sexually mature females.

Chunk Foods makes clean-label, plant-based whole cut products. By combining plant ingredients and food-grade microorganisms, the company delivers the textures, flavors, and nutritional benefits of meat without its moral and environmental costs.
Spun out of MIT, Chunk is enabling large-scale manufacturing of healthy, realistic whole muscle cut meat alternatives. Its first target is beef; seafood and poultry are next.

Cando has developed a platform based on a robust system that combines stationary sensors (on masts and tied drones) and mobile devices (a variety of drones). The platform enables the detection and investigation of threats with autonomous management and control of a multi-drone fleet.
Cando enables quick coverage of agricultural areas, forests, and nature reserves. It collects information on plant health, crops, and potential problems, allowing faster, more accurate, and cost-effective responses in order to prevent crises. Detectors and other technology installed on a variety of drones enable the collection of more information in order to quickly discover and identify various objects and bodies over large areas.

Altman Health develops a wide range of products including dietary supplements, homeopathic solutions, medicinal cosmetics, vitamins, minerals, and probiotics. The company also operates a service and training department of veteran professionals including naturopaths, nutritionists, and dietitians to respond to customer inquiries.
Altman Health is a subsidiary of Maabarot Products and was created in 2005 with the merger of Ta'am Teva and Altman.

MediCane Health is an international pharmaceutical company engaged in the research, development, production, and marketing of cannabis-based medications. With operational subsidiaries in Israel, Portugal, and a commercial hub in Germany, the company focuses on European countries that promote legislation for medical cannabis.
MediCane aims to advance medical research and development in different therapeutic areas, exploring the connection between the use of cannabis plant components and improving the health of patients with various medical conditions. MediCane wishes to contribute to the symptom relief of people whose needs cannot be met through traditional drug treatments.
column11: europe, east asia, australia, israel, united states

column3:
CopterPIX PRO specializes in designing, developing, and manufacturing advanced unmanned aerial vehicle solutions.
The company's drones fly at least 30% longer and carry at least 40% more payload than any commercial drone on the market. The drones are equipped with day/night cameras, real-time advanced image processing, precise landing, and unique ground control and docking stations.

Cambya is a botanical plant-based sweetening formula, designed to help food, confectionery, savory, beverage, dairy, and ice cream manufacturers reduce or replace sugar and other sweeteners without compromising on the final product taste.
Cambya was developed by Better Than Sweet Ltd.

Purammon is focused on the research, development, design, and implementation of physico-chemical wastewater treatment processes and systems, with special emphasis on ammonia, total nitrogen, and total organic carbon removal. Purammon systems are designed to reduce operational costs and ensure strict compliance with environmental requirements and government regulations.

The Mediterranean Food Lab's vision is to reduce dependence on animal protein by delivering plant-based products that impart and enhance flavor to a wide range of foods.
The Mediterranean Food Lab develops natural, healthy flavor bases that are sustainably produced and affordable, using novel modalities based on traditional, multi-phase, solid-state fermentation of plant protein.
foodiedo is a young startup in the FoodTech field which offers personalized nutrition solutions.

Plantish is an alternative protein company developing a breakthrough additive manufacturing technology to produce whole-cut fish fillets at low cost and massive scale.
The company’s mission is to save the oceans and eliminate the consumption of marine animals by providing better fish for humanity. Plantish aims to become the world’s leading seafood brand without ever harming a single fish.

Alfred’s Food-Tech is developing alternatives to animal proteins using a new technology for the production of plant-based meat and cheese analogues. The company’s technology mimics the flavor, texture, and mouth feel of animal-derived products as well as providing similar nutritional values.

Watrix is an AI-based leak detector. Watrix monitors the water running through pipes in the home, uses algorithms to detect any abnormal water consumption, and reacts immediately to prevent damage.
Watrix was developed by IUCO.
column12: watrix basic, watrix advanced, watrix pro, watrix combo

column3:
Growor provides a universal technological solution for indoor and greenhouse farming. Its technology allows for the manipulation of the entire growing process, leading to increased production yield, enhanced fruit quality, improved health, and repeatability with every cycle.
From lights, humidity, oxygen, and temperature to any other parameter responsible for growth, optimal growth conditions are set. Every crop receives precisely what it requires during every moment between planting and harvesting.
column11: europe, asia, canada, israel, united states

column3:
TopGum developed Gummiceuticals, a patent-pending, sugar-free, generic delivery system designed to facilitate the integration of a wide variety of nutrients.
The company's portfolio of gummies includes dietary supplements such as essential vitamins, minerals, natural extracts, and pre and probiotics. The company's nutraceuticals made from whole foods and botanicals have active ingredients to strengthen the immune system, vision, urinary health, and more.

RadarV is developing technology that will enable multiple types of unmanned aircraft systems to navigate safely in the same airspace. Its airborne radar-based detect-and-avoid (DAA) system provides drones with fully automated DAA capability and enables safe operation beyond visual line of sight.
With RadarV’s system, the radar is mounted on the drone or air mobility platform to ensure that it stays clear of manned aircraft.

Meatafora is focused on developing technology for producing a healthy, environmentally friendly, and ethical alternative to animal meat.
Meatafora aims to produce and grow cultured meat without the use of the fetal calf serum widely used in the industry, instead developing a groundbreaking line of edible carriers (scaffolds) based on vegetable protein.

Watersight's solution is a small, affordable, and connective spectral sensor that is able to scan running water in real time to alert and monitor contamination in the water supply. Watersight uses a small and powerful CMOS spectrometer-on-chip powered by artificial intelligence. The company's technology can measure a concentration of a contaminant or analyze the health or security of a flowing system in real time.
Watersight's module takes up to 4,000 multispectral images at 1,024 different wavelengths every second, enabling a huge dataset for different applications powered by machine learning. The chip features a low cost and advanced communication abilities.

The Olive Chain aims to address olive oil production fraud using decentralized processing technology. The company’s distributed blockchain solution integrates the digital and physical aspects of the olive oil industry by combining smart technologies and advanced operational optimization.
The Olive Chain’s solution is designed to achieve active engagement in the production cycle, enter real-time data as proxy, and establish new certifications, enabling asset transfer (provenance), cross-organizational workflow, and multiparty auditing. The company is also focused on technologically restoring rich oil blends and in-demand flavors.

Seambiotic aims to grow and process marine micro-algae using an ecologically based environmental system to contribute to a reduction in carbon dioxide emissions. Seambiotic has developed new research methods for cultivating various species of marine micro-algae using the carbon dioxide emissions from the Israeli Electric Corporation power plant in Ashkelon, released directly from their smokestacks, passing through pipelines directly to Seambiotic's open ponds.
column11: australia, china, india, japan, united states

column3:
TAGim is the developer of a livestock health monitoring system that automatically and remotely monitors individual animals’ temperature, movement, and feeding. The system consists of inexpensive disposable wireless ear tags and a fixed communications network and cloud database, all supported by a management dashboard and pen-rider app.
TAGim’s health-tracking algorithm reports to stakeholders and alerts pen-riders, enabling early and effective interventions days prior to the detection of symptoms using visual cues alone. The smart tags are also a surrogate for visual ID ear tags, eliminating both excess work and the need for animals to suffer additional piercings.
column11: americas, north america, central america, south america, europe, northern europe, western europe, eastern europe, southern europe, asia, north asia, central asia, west asia, east asia, southeast asia, south asia, africa, southern africa, oceania, global

column3:
BeAir is a start-up company specializing in the field of atmospheric water generation (AWG).
BeAir's specific membrane technology (patent pending) enhances existing AWG technologies, by increasing the process efficiency and removing the need for maintenance-heavy, disinfection processes and particle filtration, an inherent result of the specific, non-porous membrane used.

H2OLL is a proprietary atmospheric-moisture-harvesting technology capable of extracting moisture from the air using an absorption-desorption cycle. The technology generates a year-long pure and safe drinking water supply with constant low energy requirements in any season, geographic area, and time of day.
H2OLL aims to provide an always-on, off-grid, robust, affordable, and reliable water service to support the poorest 10% of the population. H2OLL also strives to balance the environmental impact of consuming bottled water in developed communities.

Space Plasmatics offers a plasma technology designed for use in infrastructure applications and in maneuvering nanosatellites. The technology will be launched to the International Space Station in February 2022 for testing as part of the RAKIA mission.

Teva Deli is a family-owned and operated company specializing in high-mix, low-volume production of plant-based alternative protein foods. Its mission is to deliver high-quality, cutting-edge, nutritious vegan foods in accordance with the UN Sustainable Development Goals.

Shamna Foods specializes in designing familiar food products made with functional and sustainable ingredients through the use of food industry side streams. The company’s work has led to the development of an innovative process for cold-pressing herbs that captures the essence and purity of the herbs.

Red Solar Flower (RSF) is developing semi-transparent, non-silicon solar panels for use on agricultural land, providing a synergetic and profitable dual-use solution.
The patented Perovskite-based solar panels transfer only the wavelengths required for photosynthesis while generating power from all other wavelengths, thereby enabling 100% coverage of the growing area while maintaining the light conditions required for plant growth.

Gavan's proprietary technology extracts proteins from source materials while keeping the protein's physical structure unharmed. This multi-stage technology preserves the high functionality of the protein, enables the extraction of multiple products until the source is totally consumed, and allows higher profitability from each source.
The company has proven the efficacy of its technology with spirulina algae.

SIM.SPACE develops products and provides services related to simulations, simulators, hardware-in-the-loop (HIL) hybrid labs, and electrical ground support equipment (EGSE) for the aerospace and automotive industries.

MEALA is developing new ingredients and processes designed to replace methyl cellulose and hydrocolloids in meat, egg, dairy and fish substitutes, resulting in a cleaner, healthier, tastier product with a better ecological footprint.

ALVÁTECH is the developer of a water treatment technology designed to help farmers increase both productivity and profit by growing more using less water.
The company’s technology has been proven to increase yield, improve produce quality, and even restore the soil’s fertility and biodiversity, with little or no need for fertilizers that can further damage the soil and create greenhouse gas emissions.

Fabumin has developed a patented replacement for albumin, the protein found in egg whites and a major raw material in the global food industry. Produced from food industry waste, the company’s product is natural, herbal, hypoallergenic, and sustainable, with a fully functional range similar to that of albumin and egg powder. The product consists of powdered raw material and has a long shelf life. It is also multifunctional and can be used in a variety of different foods, including sauces, bread, ice cream, pastries, and more.
Lulav Space is providing off-the-shelf vision-aided autonomous navigation and robotics systems for the aerospace industry.
PortLabs is a start-up in the emerging air taxi market. PortLabs develops a control system to increase traffic flow, safety, and profitability for multi-stakeholders in the industry.

Bountica develops food-safe and nature-based proteins that prevent the decay and spoilage of perishable foods and beverages, reduce food loss by extending their storage and shelf life, and benefit both consumers and producers.
Bountica is bringing together pharmaceutical drug-discovery technologies with industry best practices and application insights to solve significant challenges in the agriculture, food, and animal health sectors.
Terra Space Lab is developing a nanosatellite-based infrared earth observation system.

ScoutX is a support platform designed for vineyards and the global grape market. The company uses AI-driven technology and smart optical sensors to increase grape yields and improve profitability by enabling the prediction and early detection of plant diseases and stress before crops are harmed.

Egg'n'up is a food technology company developing a sustainable alternative egg product using proprietary plant-based ingredients to get the unique taste, texture, appearance, and functionality of eggs without compromising on taste or nutritional value.
Egg'n'up is a subsidiary of SavorEat.

Eggmented Reality has developed a technological platform for the precision fermentation of non-genetically-modified functional proteins for the food industry. The company’s first product will be a vegan version of ovalbumin, the main protein in egg whites.
Eggmented Reality was founded by Dr. Itamar Yadid and Itay Bloch from the Migal Galilee Research Institute.

YieldX is a Bio-AIoT platform provider specializing in livestock production efficiency. Using IoT devices that require no additional input from farmers, YieldX creates an information infrastructure that enables users to know everything about their poultry production environment in real time.
In addition to monitoring production, tracking employee location, and connecting third-party machinery, the platform makes real-time digested data available to domain experts, enabling them to make cost-effective, real-time decisions for increasing yields, reducing costs, enforcing biosecurity protocols, and identifying and fixing production issues on the spot.

Nevatim Super Food developed "Merelin farms," indoor farms that operate technological breeding facilities for growing selected green foods, independent of climate conditions. Nevatim's goal is to enable the growing of nutritious and quality food.
Nevatim's technological farms include smart lighting, climate control systems, probiotic bacteria dispersal, moisture-assisted irrigation, gases to eliminate mold, and many other solutions to produce healthy food at scale.

Sea2Cell is developing a sustainable cell-cultured fish using immortalized fish cell lines with improved proliferation rates. The cells differentiate according to a specifically designed signal, reducing overall costs and enabling efficient scale-up.

E-FISHient Protein develops cultured fish meat for human consumption that is cleaner and lower cost than standard grown fish.
E-FISHient aims to develop a clean environment with toxin-free water, reduce pressure on wild fisheries, eliminate the need for foreign imports, and enhance food security.
E-FISHient Protein is a joint venture of Biomeat Foodtech and Volcani Center.

PoLoPo is a biotech startup developing an economical platform for high-scale production of proteins in plants. The company’s technology is focused on using directed metabolic engineering to create a “superAA” plant capable of producing extremely high amounts of free amino acids.
The elevated production of amino acids is then translated into high-scale production of proteins. In this second phase, superAA plants are used as the basis for creating a new set of plants by expressing and accumulating the target proteins in plant sink organs.

H4Bees is an emerging company dedicated to the research, development, and commercialization of proprietary medicine for bees.
The company developed an H4Bees compound that enhances bees' strength, honey yield per hive, and pollination effectiveness. H4Bees is a natural, ecological, easy-to-apply powder for beehives, proven to boost hives' health and productivity.
column11: north america, europe, east asia, southeast asia

column3:
Mermade Seafoods is a cellular aquaculture company specializing in the production of cell-based seafood. The company's approach enables the mass production of cultured seafood using a fermentation-based process that results in clean, healthy, and sustainable protein-rich seafood products.
Mermade Seafoods aims to be the first company to provide a circular method of production using side-stream valorization of growth media. The company's technology is based on upcycling biological waste products from spent growth media into new, nutrient-rich food for the growing cells.

Innovaero aims to improve the lives of people worldwide by changing the way they travel for work and leisure. The company is developing the Pentax, a patent-pending two-ton air vehicle designed to carry four passengers.

Via Cool provides a solution for accurately predicting the shelf life and quality of fresh fruits and vegetables. The company has developed a platform that utilizes big data and proprietary scientific knowledge and algorithms to provide valuable commercial insights, enabling supply chains to make precise operational and business decisions while reducing the amount of food waste.

AIR develops everyday mobility solutions for everyday people, developing passenger electric aircraft with vertical take-off and landing capabilities.
The company's AirOne offers a sleek, streamlined design with the 'fly by intent' system. AIR's solutions require minimal training and uphold the highest safety standards.

Cyanotech is the founder of Cyamonia Bio, which is focused on disrupting the current organic food market by introducing an innovative, cutting-edge technology for producing high-nitrogen fertilizer from the atmosphere using nitrogen-fixing cyanobacteria.
The company’s automated photo-bioreactors operate on-site to produce ammonia from the air using the sun as an energy source. The technology is designed to greatly increase the availability of precision organic fertilizer for food growers worldwide while dramatically reducing the huge carbon footprint of fertilizers produced using the Haber Bosch process.
TUMA is helping to extend the life shelf of very sensitive ag products such as figs, cherry tomatoes, cannabis and more.

BioTip has developed a solution designed to indicate a product’s freshness. The company’s freshness stickers use a small bag containing a sample of the product along with biochemicals whose reaction to the sample causes the sticker to change color according to the product’s state of freshness.
BioTip’s freshness stickers contain only compounds approved for use in the food industry.

FortePhest is a biotechnology start-up developing a technology to combat herbicide‐resistant weeds.
FortePhest is developing H-Forte, a herbicide leveraging a recently discovered mechanism of action. H-Forte was inspired by natural plant protectors that can delay or completely inhibit the development of weeds. H-Forte targets a key enzyme of protein synthesis, phenylalanine tRNA synthetase. H-Forte is intended to control resistant weeds by disrupting the structure of their proteins.

Viator Engineering is developing a versatile VTOL UAV with hybrid-electric propulsion technology. The innovative hybrid drone model has a compact, aerodynamic design with a smart power-energy management system that enables economically viable, high-payload aircraft capability for significant distances, as well as high-speed flight safety and suitability for urban intracity, city-to-city, and far-field use.

SustainIO aims to reduce food waste by introducing and enabling “Precision nutrition”.
SustainIO develops a cloud-based application which will analyze volatile molecules that are produced as food ages.
Biofood Systems has developed a line of meat analogues based on plant protein that are designed to replicate the four components in real meat: muscle, fat, connective tissue, and blood.
column11: americas, europe, southeast asia, northern africa, china

column3:
NematoEat has developed an economical, highly effective biological solution against destructive root-knot nematodes. The company’s technology is based a predatory nematode that eats the eggs and the juveniles of root-knot nematodes. The predatory nematode is added to the soil, dramatically reducing crop infestation.
NematoEat is a fully-owned subsidiary of COPIA Agro and Food Technologies Fund.
column11: south america, europe, asia, oceania, israel, united states

column3: FarmGuests is designed for enthusiastic travelers interested in agritourism. FarmGuests' platform allows tourists and business owners to find, reach, and communicate with each other. Farmers, ranchers, and winery owners can use FarmGuests to share the rural entertainment, excursions, farm shops, and volunteer opportunities their land has to offer.

COPIA Magnificent has developed a simple, safe, and natural method for reducing or inhibiting the formation of biofilms.
Biofilms are highly structured multicellular communities that allow bacteria to survive hostile environments, pasteurization, and preservatives and have been linked to the contamination of milk, beverages, food products, and the surfaces of processing equipment.

FlyWorks has developed and patented a way to power multi-rotor drones using a petrol engine. The technology combines the performance of petrol fuel with the safety and simplicity of the multi-rotor platform. It works by delivering most of the power that the drone requires to stay in the air directly from an internal combustion engine, while a small electric drive system provides a small fraction of power only for maneuvering.

Water Innovations is developing an underground device that enables fast water insertion in hard-to-penetrate, thin-grain soils, preventing water from evaporating and ensuring that trees get access to a source of water for an extended period of time.

PhloemAid has developed a control measure for use against phloem bacterial pathogens. Phloem-restricted bacteria cause billions of dollars in damage annually due to lower yield and product quality in crops infected by diseases such as grapevine yellows, citrus greening disease, and lethal yellowing disease in coconuts. Phloem pathogens are associated with diseases in hundreds of plant species, including economically important food crops such as vegetables, fruit, and ornamentals, as well as timber and shade trees.

SoilFender develops crop protection solutions based on fungal volatile organic compounds (VOCs) that are highly effective against numerous crop pathogens.
Endophytic fungi are micro-organisms that spend most of their life cycle within plant tissues without causing any damage to the host plants. Many endophytes secrete metabolites that, in addition to assisting the fungi to survive inside the plant, confer fitness benefits to their hosts, such as growth enhancement and tolerance to biotic and abiotic stresses.

Vitalgia develops robotic systems for heated greenhouses and vertical farming. The company's mission is to maximize plant yields by taking timely action tailored to each plant's specific needs and replacing costly human labor.
Vitalgia's products and technology help enable precise operations through the use of in-depth plant analysis and can be used to expand and diversify the range of cultivars grown through vertical farming.

Aerodrome offers a fully modified, comprehensive solution for unmanned aircraft systems (UAS), including a training and operations program. The company provides a full line of services for defense industries and organizations that wish to use unmanned systems.
Aerodrome finances, operates, offers basic and advanced training, and provides integrated logistics support (ILS) with an additional package of services for the successful implementation of UAS technologies and sensors.

Creomagic develops autonomous and intelligent mobile ad-hoc networks (MANETs), providing comprehensive wireless communication solutions for the most demanding environments.
The company’s solutions enable the transmission of high-quality real-time video, voice, and data exchange for mission-critical, safety-critical applications within a private, secure, and reliable network and without the need for any permanent infrastructure.

CyWat Technologies develops cyber-like physical water protection systems for the water-monitoring industry and water authorities, with the endorsement of the Israeli government.
The company offers water suppliers across the globe a solution for real-time water quality monitoring, preventing water pollution events and ensuring public health and safety.

Sufresca develops edible coatings for produce, facilitating longer shelf life and reducing post-harvest loss and waste. Sufresca's coatings are tailored to each targeted fruit or vegetable, using specific liquid formulations suitable for both traditional and organic agriculture.
Sufresca develops coatings for tomatoes, cucumbers, peppers, garlic bulbs, pomegranate seeds, and more.

Foodup Monitoring develops a real-time monitoring and information gathering system for the food, pharmaceutical and agricultural industries. The system is custom made for production managers, food engineers or quality assurance managers.
It improves the working ranges, process alert capability and real-time malfunctions. It is a tool for optimizing the production system - identifying production trends, quality and food safety and in-depth analysis by charts and analysis tables. The system can utilize existing sensors in the factory systems.

Zo-opt is a provider and developer of plankton-sized, live feed products for fish larvae, produced in a natural, biological process. The company produces live protozoa in sizes ranging between 40-100 micrometer, for larval feeding.
Zo-opt's technology is a breakthrough in bringing new ocean species into industrial harvesting.

FishBreed develops therapeutic agents to overcome fish reproductive dysfunctions. Its therapeutic agents can be used to accelerate the onset of puberty by which an immature fish acquires for the first time the capacity to reproduce.

MyCrops provides smart crop monitoring tools that deliver insights for preventing crop loss and getting plants on track for maximum yields. The company’s deep learning algorithms for predictive analytics are based on unique data sets generated from hundreds of thousands of mobile app users.
MyCrops’ spot-imaging solution captures automated 24/7, 360° views of every plant in order to provide daily decision support, providing users with clear dashboard views to help their entire team increase performance.

SELFLY.Camera has developed the camera-equipped SELFLY phone case drone. SELFLY enables users to take selfies using a smart drone attached seamlessly to their smartphones.
The drone folds out of a flush, protective, 9-millimeter-thick phone case. SELFLY hovers autonomously, but can be controlled from the user’s smartphone, which also displays real-time transmissions from the drone’s camera.
ResourCycle develops technology for the global waste management industry.

Tomaisins International has developed seeds for growing raisin tomatoes (tomatoes that are naturally dried while still on the plant). The raisin tomatoes contain up to 10 times more lycopene than ordinary cherry tomatoes.

Aero-Z-Comm has developed a wireless communication for use inside airplanes.
The patented technology applies an infrared networking system and use of smart Mini IR transceivers.
The invention is based on an aeronautical cellular network and includes a cellular telephone system for use within an aircraft, for the applied telecom standards such as GSM or DCS systems.

Tikun Olam specializes in breeding proprietary cannabis strains and developing standardized, accurately dosed products. The company’s production techniques are focused on increasing the efficacy of the plant’s active ingredients. Tikun Olam’s products are used in a number of ongoing clinical trials in Israel’s regulated medical cannabis market.
Tikun Olam also operates Tikun Olam Care, a professional cannabis nursing clinic that provides safe and personalized treatment for a variety of medical conditions to more than 20,000 patients of all ages.
column11: australia, brazil, canada, greece, israel, united kingdom, united states

column3:
Controlled Irrigation Technologies (C.I.T.) aims to increase irrigation efficiency in the agricultural and urban sectors. Its products function as autonomous learning systems based on an algorithm with control and feedback functions.
C.I.T. offers irrigation control systems for shallow-rooted plants and deep-rooted crops. The control systems use sensors to scan the ground, system management control to track irrigation pace and frequency, and an algorithm that decides the necessary actions to be taken.

EcoBreed develops solutions to fast-track natural plant breeding. The company's technological platform, BreedFit, enables rapid and personalized breeding of plant varieties by learning the farmer's field and its specific environmental conditions.
When introduced into a new field, the BreedFit system uses big data and artificial intelligence to assess various factors such as unique markers for local adaptation. The system then recommends specific varieties for breeding based on its analysis.

Bright Agtech is the developer of an innovative solution for the precision treatment of field crops against weeds, pests, and diseases. The company’s fees are based on the type of service and coverage area, and the farmer is not required to buy or operate any equipment.
Bright Agtech’s solution can save farmers up to 30% of the overall cost of treatment as well as about 70% of the amount of herbicides/pesticides conventionally used.
column12: bright agtech precision treatment for field crops

column3: This company is a known business entity but lacks sufficient data to support a standard Finder profile

Agrogreen was a biotech company that was backed by the Minrav Group—a large Israeli infrastructure and engineering company. The company's biotech unit produced a product to protect crops from harmful nematodes. The technology was initially licensed from the Volcani Institute.

Amplio connects students, educators, and administrators with advanced technologies to help students with special needs maximize their potential and improve outcomes. Amplio's digital platform equips students with individualized, high-fidelity interventions and enables educators to devote more time to direct instruction. Administrators gain a 360-degree view into student progress, resources, compliance, and funding.

WeeeDrive is a mobile app using behavioral science to influence the way young people drive. WeeeDrive creates customized driving courses for each driver according to their personal capabilities and instructs them in real time on every ride.
WeeeDrive aims to improve driving skills and reduce insurance claims and premiums.

Radix assists administrators, support engineers, project leaders, parents, teachers, vendors, and private users by keeping them informed about mobile-device activity. The company also delivers tools for system management optimization, including monitoring, support, policy enforcement, and screen control on single and multiple computing devices.
Radix aims to make organizations' mobile devices more effective, secure, and manageable. In education, this means maximizing the pedagogical effectiveness of the mobile-device learning platform; in the business world, it involves achieving operational efficiency.

Spectalix helps content app owners reclaim users through a disruptive AI video technology. Offered as either an SDK or a white label app, the company’s technology enables content app owners to upload short clips (”scenes”) featuring their talent/players to their apps. Owners can then invite users to place themselves within the scenes and act in them in real time, without a green screen, using only a smartphone.
Unlike large social networks and user-generated content, Spectalix’s technology increases customer traffic and user engagement both by enabling the creation of quality content and by enticing users to interact with celebrities. Spectalix also creates exceptional new revenue sources for app owners, as they can sell this highly interactive activity to sponsors and advertisers or even charge users directly.

Bites develops solutions for training, communications, and everything else a frontline workforce requires. It is based on a content creation app that enables managers to easily create media-based professional units and seamless delivery of the units to employees via familiar channels such as WhatsApp, Slack, SMS, and Microsoft Teams.
Bites operates worldwide with customers across a range of industries and currently has more than 29,000 active users.

DigitalRosh is a professional community platform catering to digital leaders. DigitalRosh is sponsored by i8 Ventures and Accenture and maintains an academic partnership with the Technion as part of an ongoing effort to strengthen digital and innovation skills within organizations.

Edocate is the developer of a virtual patient simulation (VPS) platform designed to provide evidence-based training on long-term patient care in a realistic yet risk-free virtual world. Unlike many other VPS platforms on the market, Edocate offers an unbounded simulation experience that is automatically driven by smart algorithms and evidence-based engines to simulate disease progression, the effects of medication, and the onset of side effects.
column11: north america, europe, southeast asia, israel

column3: Jolt is a business school designed specifically for self-made professionals. The company operates a network of campuses offering professional video courses to tech workers at every career stage. The courses are presented by internationally acclaimed experts and executives from leading tech companies, including Amazon, Google, Linkedin, and Netflix. Jolt’s mission is to give each of its students a competitive advantage.

Shuffll is a platform for creators based on a content-oriented game engine, allowing anyone to instantly create professional and interactive entertainment shows, such as dating shows, music contests, trivia nights, debates, sports shows, and many others.

Toya is female-led studio that develops video games and virtual goods inspired by the life stories of pioneering women. The company is currently focusing on Roblox, a powerful community-driven platform featuring democratic gameplay and an avid female audience. Toya’s games include My Farm, a farming game simulating the economics of multinational farms; and Miraculous, a Roblox game with superheroes as characters.
column12: my farm, my cat box, miraculous

column3: Lightricks provides solutions for the mobile market, developing fun and powerful visual editing apps for content creators. The company’s award-winning apps are used by millions of smartphone users globally.
column12: enlight videoleap, enlight photofox, enlight quickshot, facetune 2, enlight pixaloop, beatleap, filtertune, quicktart

column3:
Proprep is an education technology company that develops video content, including thousands of exercises, powered by a technology that customizes courses in science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) according to the specific needs of university students and institutions of higher education.
The company operates worldwide under a variety of brands, including Gool in Israel, Proprep in the United States, and Proprep UK in the United Kingdom.
column11: israel, nigeria, united kingdom, united states, vietnam

column3:
Uniper Care Technologies creates solutions for elderly people at home or in care facilities to have dignified, connected, and fun experiences. The company promotes active aging through its accessible, AI-based IoT technology. The platform enables elderly people to keep doing what they love, without having to change habits, leave home, or adopt new technologies or devices.
Uniper's Android-based set-top box turns any TV into an aging-in-place platform. Its holistic services include social engagement, assistance with performing daily activities, access to entertainment content, and management of medical needs.

Makeree is an interactive environment for learning and teaching creative skills. By providing branded instructional apps to manufacturers, the company allows users to learn hands-on skills and create interactions between manufacturers and their customers.

Stops is a geospatial search engine that delivers time- and location-based results for smart devices, smart cars, and smart communities. The platform’s relevant, location-based results include Wikipedia, Yelp, Google Places, Meetup, YouTube videos, Spotify songs, news items, and more.
Users can filter their searches, follow each other, and view their results on 3D maps and in augmented reality. In addition, users can create and collect their own stops for travel itineraries or real estate listings, privately message each other, and store their geo-based data securely on the cloud, with full security control and GDPR compliance.

column3:
G-Med is a global physician-only community, reaching over 1 million verified physicians from more than 120 countries and 100 specialties. The company's medical crowdsourcing platform enables physicians from all over the world to collaborate to solve patient cases and earn honoraria from surveys and market research.
G-Med's members can connect with local and global opinion leaders, participate in online educational activities, use peer-to-peer consultations to solve clinical dilemmas, and get answers from verified physicians in the relevant specialty. Members can use the power of the global medical community to shorten the diagnostic time and improve healthcare.
column11: global, argentina, brazil, chile, colombia, ecuador, el salvador, peru, south africa, venezuela

column3:
MyPart is an AI-powered song search and matching platform.
MyPart's award-winning technology uses reference songs rather than conventional tagging techniques to help industry professionals prioritize their musical catalogs and discover new talent. This helps them find songs that share common harmonic, melodic, lyrical, sonic, and structural features with their predefined benchmarks, and ensures they only listen to the songs that match their needs.

WhileFly's technology enables low-cost airlines to serve their passengers with free on-board content and entertainment during the flight.
WhileFly provides the look and feel of the internet with fresh content and videos. Users can also book products and services while on board, all using no or narrow-band connectivity without degradation of the user experience.

Tunity developed an application that allows users to hear live audio from muted televisions directly on their mobile devices. Through patented deep-learning and computer-vision technology, Tunity identifies a live video stream and its exact timing, syncing the audio with the user's mobile device.
The company (formerly known as AudioStreamTV) was selected to receive the "One to Watch" award at the 2014 NVIDIA Emerging Companies Summit.

Sidelines is a sports technology and digital media platform dedicated to helping users make smart, data-driven sports betting decisions. The platform offers users a visual analysis of sports betting using technology that is able to identify and present price differences and market opportunities to anyone who is interested, at no cost.
Sidelines is developed by Fantasy Advantage, a subsidiary of Natural Intelligence.

JobSwipe is an app that matches people with jobs through a user interface similar to Tinder's, while incentivizing sharing and engagement through referral bonuses. JobSwipe users simply upload their résumés once and choose their skills and location preferences. From there, JobSwipe searches in more than 200 Facebook and LinkedIn groups.
Users swipe to apply for a job, reducing transaction costs and making the process of applying for a job fun and engaging. In addition, recruiters can put a referral bonus on their job postings, incentivizing users to swipe and refer their friends. The app displays shared Facebook connections to create trust, generate interest, and make referrals easier.

muzy is a musical language app that translates the classical note system into an intuitive visual one. The app can translate any song into the muzy language, making it quick and easy to play.
The muzy app was developed by Musical Notes.

HASHMUGS has developed an augmented reality app designed and developed for the coffee industry. Its mobile app allows coffee lovers, social-network enthusiasts, and coffee brands to engage with augmented reality content while enjoying their coffee moments.
HASHMUGS is a proud impact partner of Coffee Kids, a leading Brooklyn-based nonprofit providing training, mentoring, and financial support to young coffee farmers in developing countries. HASHMUGS gives the community the opportunity to become part of a global movement of coffee lovers with the power to raise awareness and contribute to high-impact projects.

Motionbee is a graphic design and video production service that is committed to creating buzz. With a flat-rate monthly subscription model, Motionbee offers its clients unlimited service requests and revisions across all of their video, digital, print, web, and branding needs.

WSC Sports Technologies has developed a platform designed to generate personalized sports videos for every digital platform and sports fan, automatically and in real time.
The WSC Sports platform utilizes advanced artificial intelligence and machine learning technologies to analyze live sports broadcasts, identify each and every event that occurs in the game, create customized short-form video content, and publish to any digital destination.

Village is the developer of a social music-sharing platform that enables users to create “villages” – online communities that curate an up-voted playlist by sharing and voting on their favorite music together.

radd. develops solutions that enable online customers and influencers to show brand affinity via video stories directly uploaded to eCommerce sites. The company’s vision is to connect online buyers with desired products by offering a personalized, live, and interactive shopping experience. Its solution offers a social way to shop online, providing eCommerce stores with an automated tool that can boost customer- and influencer-generated content, drive conversion rates, and pull in new traffic.

Poney provides an application that teaches children how to save wisely and spend smartly. Parents who would like to teach their children how to be responsible for their financial decisions can utilize Poney as an educational application.
Poney enables parents to view their children’s purchase history, including which vendors their children have purchased products from. Parents may also assign chores to their children and reward them with an allowance. With Poney, children can learn how to save up for items on their wish list.

Namez allows users to record their own name or the name of their product or company for use on any online platform. The user simply records once and can then publish the recorded file everywhere – on social profiles, email signatures, blogs, websites, and even in logos. The recording is showcased in an attractive button that users will be happy to share.
Namez helps eliminate the mispronunciation of products, places, companies, and more. By educating their audience, Namez users can impart the particular sense of relief and satisfaction that comes with learning how an unfamiliar name or word is pronounced. In addition, once people hear how a name is pronounced, they are more likely to remember it.

Travless provides deals, coupons, and local offers to travelers worldwide. The company has created a massive database system that uses smart-filtering solutions and a machine-learning engine to customize and display the right information to the right people.
The Travless database contains information from local businesses, as well as direct connections created by the Travless sales and marketing team. The data compiled in the system is based on incentives and an understanding of the market’s specific needs.

Our goal is Human connection. Anonypo has the approach of putting you in the centre, providing you with tools to make real life connections in real time. The ingredients in our formula consist of real time, eyesight range, anonymity and some salt and pepper.
With Anonypo you're completely anonymous, so feel free to speak your mind and share your thoughts. Your next business opportunity, roommate or friend might be a few steps away from you, but how will you know if you're not connected to them on any network? Anonypo connects you with everyone around you. The rest is up to you.

Blinq is a mobile app that enhances users’ existing messaging apps. Blinq helps make conversations more personal and relevant by providing users with a stream of insights and updates on those who matter to them, such as work colleagues, business prospects, family, and friends.
With Blinq, users can save time, enrich their messaging apps, and stay up-to-date on the important events taking place in the lives of those around them.

KeyBoots provides a social platform for travelers who are seeking places to stay in exchange for volunteer work. The company was established with the goal of creating a new way of traveling that benefits both local organizations and travelers.
With the KeyBoots platform, users can search for host families to volunteer with in exchange for room and board, and in some cases pocket money as well. KeyBoots gives young, eager travelers a way to see the world by providing a tool that lets them interact with enterprises that can use their efforts and talents, promoting a mutually beneficial experience.

Qaviton is a platform for automation testing that uses machine learning to speed the authoring, execution, and maintenance of automated tests. Based on Selenium and Appium, the platform enables developers to automate the manual testing process and reduce costs, improve product quality, and accelerate delivery.

Vub It! is a video-messaging application designed for iOS and Android that lets users communicate with their friends in an innovative, humorous way by allowing them to record their own voices over clips from their favorite movies and TV shows.
Vub It was designed by AMS Technologies Ltd.

Novabu provides a mobile platform and a smart database for credible product grading. Novabu’s platform allows customers to grade the food dishes they’ve ordered and then share their reviews with others. In this way, the application enables customers to make informed decisions about where to eat based on previous customers’ actual experiences.
Novabu is committed to supplying its users with credible information, and has developed technology and algorithms that ensure that only the most accurate and trustworthy information is entered into the database. Grades are added only upon proof of purchase and weighted according to their quality and effectiveness.

AppMyDay, an individualized event and photo-sharing platform, allows event hosts to create a unique social network, where guests can interact within the event through photo sharing and more.
With AppMyDay, each guest becomes a photographer, making every event an interactive celebration. Anyone with event access can view the event’s pictures in real-time, rather than continuously searching for pictures on various social platforms such as Facebook and Instagram.
column11: europe, hong kong, israel, united states

column3:
Surge is an online platform designed to provide continuing medical education for all doctors, everywhere. Surge aims to reduce the burden of medical complications and preventable errors through high-quality online educational programs, certificates, and degrees.
Surge's platform enables doctors to meet their annual educational requirements, learn innovative surgical techniques, and improve their patient outcomes. With Surge, doctors can view procedures directly from the operating room as well as submit their own complex cases and receive guidance from instructors.

Indiepush is a platform where independent artists can efficiently market their music directly to their fans. The sharing-focused platform also allows fans to market to their family and friends, as well as to get rewarded for experiencing music interactively.
Through Indiepush, fans have the opportunity to earn points for sharing their favorite artists’ music, enabling them to show support for artists while also benefitting themselves. Fans can purchase music with the points they earn from sharing music.

Retto.me is the developer of Retto (Japanese for “vote”), an online community that offers music-related products, links, and websites which it updates on a daily basis. On Retto, users can vote and post their opinions on the products listed, as well as share them with other music lovers.
Content is posted to Retto daily, enabling users to continually make new musical discoveries. Retto was conceived with the intention of building a large music community sharing the most useful, current, and inspiring music-related content.
1-2-Trip is a mobile app that enables its users to book an entire vacation based on their budget and not the destination in 3 steps.

Proverb works worldwide in the field of digital cultural heritage to develop technological solutions for cultural institutions and organizations. The company’s focus is on how developers and experts can use technology toward improving the moment when a person meets a masterpiece, while balancing both the visitor’s needs and the special criteria applying to works of art.
Proverb is dedicated to exploring what should and can be done with the challenge of art, culture, and museums in the future, including how art institutions will use technological tools to deal with the increasing number of visitors in the coming years, as well as what technical features will ensure that the experience meets those visitors’ expectations and needs.

LiveTrip has developed a tourism platform based on interactive video streaming, offering users access to live content from experienced tour guides, shared experiences and information from other travelers, real-time information from tourist sites, and more.
LiveTrip helps users find the experiences they are looking for, provides them with the opportunity to view places before visiting them, and assists them in locating the best tour guides in a given area.
column11: australia, israel, united kingdom, united states

column3:
Nexmii is a cross-cultural social media platform where people from every corner of the world can connect to share their languages and culture with each other.
On Nexmii, users can find their own language-exchange partners through a personalized matching process, and then interact with them through real-time mini-games and live video chat.

Qubi.tech offers image-based navigation designed to adapt to every screen type, including 3D, enabling users to display information intuitively and efficiently.
The company has two main products, Qubi and iSphere. Qubi is a content-reader app that combines news feeds and the social web in a single app, allowing interactive, game-like 3D presentation of content.

Sea Tact is an online platform that allows users to experience a tactical sailing adventure without any logistical preparations or complex coordination. Players need only a smartphone or tablet to go sailing. The mobile devices serve as consoles, but it is the boats themselves that users actually navigate. Players can sail alone or with several boats together.
The races/games are monitored and controlled by the Sea Tact servers, which use the players’ GPS devices to track the participants and to display a map of the match on the players’ screens. They also monitor compliance with the rules of the game, declare penalties, and determine the winners.

DoroTree Technologies provides software created to meet the needs of users researching Jewish genealogy. The company’s product includes features such as commemoration of the Holocaust, date conversion, bilingual reports, and Jewish lineage entry, as well as an easy-to-navigate interface.

Ligature develops, markets, and supports optical character recognition (OCR) technologies and applications.
Ligature works with OEMs, VARs, and system integrators to incorporate their product, CharacterEyes, into software applications and hardware products, providing OCR-based solutions for specialized markets.

ComeToArt has developed HeART, a multimedia app for lovers of art and cultural institutions. With HeART, users can see more art, experience it the way they like, and express themselves at the same time.
HeART allows users to locate an art venue or choose an exhibition and either view specific works of art on their own or follow a tour. HeART’s artwork experience is based on different moods, categories, and media for an enlightening and personalized experience.

PicaScreen provides a complete presentation suite focused on the Sales & Business professional. Our web-based sales acceleration platform enables a seamless interaction with customers resulting in higher sales and closure rates.
We provide our users with a smart and simple solution to present and control PowerPoint Presentations and to prepare and present picture slide shows from their smart phones to any smart screen.

Tripper360, is a smart platform that helps you plan your trip without any effort, based on your interests.
You simply provide the platform with how many days you're spending; your interests; choose whether you're interesting in guided/customized tours and our smart algorithm will give you the best options for an optimized trip.
In addition, we offer you the best deals for accommodations, flights, rentals, and more...
